{"title_page": "Endorsements in the 2016 United Kingdom European Union membership referendum", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2020}}\n{{Brexit sidebar}}\n{{Expand list|date=April 2016}}\nA number of politicians, public figures, newspapers and magazines, businesses and other organisations endorsed either the United Kingdom remaining in the EU or the United Kingdom leaving the EU during the [[2016 United Kingdom European Union membership referendum]].\n\n==Remain==\n\n===Government===\n\n====Territories voting in referendum====\n* [[Government of the United Kingdom]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eureferendum.gov.uk/|title=EU Referendum \u2013 Information from the UK Government|publisher=[[Government of the United Kingdom]]|date=26 May 2016|accessdate=19 June 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Scottish Government]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-36383590|title=EU referendum debate: MSPs vote overwhelmingly for UK to remain in EU|date=26 May 2016 |accessdate=27 May 2016|work=BBC News}}</ref>\n* [[Welsh Government]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gov.wales/newsroom/firstminister/2016/160518fmwales/?lang=en|title=Statement by the First Minister of Wales: Moving Wales Forward|date=18 May 2016|accessdate=27 May 2016|author=Carwyn Jones|author-link=Carwyn Jones}}</ref>\n* [[Government of Gibraltar]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.euroweeklynews.com/3.0.15/news/on-euro-weekly-news/gibraltar-news/137143-gibraltar-government-to-support-%E2%80%98stay%E2%80%99-vote-in-eu-referendum |title=Gibraltar Government to support 'STAY' vote in EU Referendum |website=Euroweeklynews.com |accessdate=3 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n====Other Crown dependencies====\n* [[Government of Jersey]]\n* [[Government of Guernsey]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.itv.com/news/channel/2016-05-23/jersey-and-guernsey-governments-support-uk-remaining/|title=Jersey and Guernsey governments support UK remaining in EU|website=ITV.com |accessdate=24 May 2016}}</ref>\n\n====Non-UK governments====\n* [[Government of Ireland]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2016/jun/20/ireland-fearful-neighbour-leaving-eu-northern-ireland|title=Why Ireland is so fearful of our closest neighbour leaving the EU|date=20 June 2016|access-date=13 February 2018|newspaper=The Guardian}}</ref>\n* [[Government of Japan]]\n* [[Government of Indonesia]]\n\n===Registered political parties===\n'''Parties organised in more than one of the Home Nations:'''\n* [[Green Party of England and Wales]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://policy.greenparty.org.uk/eu.html |title=The Green Party Europe}}</ref>\n* [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour Party]]<ref>{{cite web|author=Patrick Wintour |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/jun/18/alan-johnson-to-head-labour-yes-campaign-for-eu-referendum |title=Alan Johnson to head Labour Yes campaign for EU referendum |work=The Guardian|accessdate=18 June 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Left Unity (UK)|Left Unity]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Another Europe is Possible: Left Unity and the EU Referendum|url=http://leftunity.org/another-europe-is-possible-left-unity-and-the-eu-referendum/|publisher=Left Unity|accessdate=8 June 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrats]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.libdems.org.uk/nick_clegg_pro_europeans_are_the_real_reformers_now |title=Nick Clegg: Pro-Europeans are the real reformers now |publisher=Libdems.org.uk |date=9 May 2014 |accessdate=12 June 2015}}</ref>\n\n'''Parties in Scotland:'''\n* [[Scottish National Party]] (SNP)<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-32961729 |title=Nicola Sturgeon warns of EU exit 'backlash' |work=BBC News |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date= 2 June 2015|accessdate=12 June 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/SNP/11621866/Alex-Salmond-Ill-campaign-with-Tories-to-stay-in-EU.html |title=Alex Salmond: I'll campaign with Tories to stay in EU |work=The Daily Telegraph|date= 21 May 2015|accessdate=27 May 2015|last1=Johnson |first1=Simon }}</ref>\n* [[Scottish Green Party]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scottishgreens.org.uk/uncategorized/eu-referendum-greens-to-make-progressive-case-for-membership/|title=\u00bb EU Referendum: Greens to Make Progressive Case for Membership|date=10 October 2015|publisher=Scottish Greens|accessdate=8 December 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117024353/https://www.scottishgreens.org.uk/uncategorized/eu-referendum-greens-to-make-progressive-case-for-membership/|archivedate=17 November 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Scottish Socialist Party]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scottishsocialistparty.org/the-socialist-case-against-leaving-the-european-union/|title=The Socialist Case Against Leaving the European Union|work=Scottish Socialist Party|date=15 February 2016}}</ref>\n\n'''Parties in Northern Ireland:'''\n* [[Alliance Party of Northern Ireland]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://allianceparty.org/article/2015/0009715/dickson-an-eu-referendum-will-threaten-jobs-and-investment-in-northern-ireland|title=Dickson \u2013 An EU referendum will threaten jobs and investment in Northern Ireland|date=14 May 2015|publisher=The Alliance Party of Northern Ireland|accessdate=8 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117024840/http://allianceparty.org/article/2015/0009715/dickson-an-eu-referendum-will-threaten-jobs-and-investment-in-northern-ireland|archive-date=17 November 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://allianceparty.org/article/2015/0009695/alliance-expresses-concerns-over-referendum-idea|title=Alliance expresses concerns over referendum idea|date=29 April 2015|publisher=The Alliance Party of Northern Ireland|accessdate=8 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117030051/http://allianceparty.org/article/2015/0009695/alliance-expresses-concerns-over-referendum-idea|archive-date=17 November 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* [[Green Party in Northern Irela