0160617094046/https://www.partyof.wales/europe-1/|archivedate=17 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n'''Parties in Gibraltar:'''\n* [[Gibraltar Social Democrats]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://chronicle.gi/2016/01/feetham-urges-joint-strategies-with-govt-on-key-issues/ |title=Feetham urges joint strategies with Govt on key issues \u2013 Gibraltar Chronicle |website=Chronicle.gi |accessdate=3 March 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303052920/http://chronicle.gi/2016/01/feetham-urges-joint-strategies-with-govt-on-key-issues/ |archive-date=3 March 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[Gibraltar Socialist Labour Party]]<ref name=\"chronicle1\">{{cite web |url=http://chronicle.gi/2016/01/garcia-flags-constitutional-reform-and-brexit-in-new-year-message/ |title=Garcia flags constitutional reform and Brexit in New Year message \u2013 Gibraltar Chronicle |website=Chronicle.gi |accessdate=3 March 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303053116/http://chronicle.gi/2016/01/garcia-flags-constitutional-reform-and-brexit-in-new-year-message/ |archive-date=3 March 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[Liberal Party of Gibraltar]]<ref name=\"chronicle1\"/>\n\n'''Other regional parties:'''\n* [[Mebyon Kernow]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mebyonkernow.org/articles/article.php?id=98|title=My initial view on the EU referendum|author=Mebyon Kernow \u2013 The Party for Cornwall|work=mebyonkernow.org}}</ref>\n\n===Business leaders===\n\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n*Sir [[Terry Leahy]], former CEO of [[Tesco]].<ref name=\"bbc.co.uk1\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-eu-referendum-36352370|title=EU referendum: Cameron warns prices would rise if UK leaves EU|date=22 May 2016|work=BBC News}}</ref>\n*[[Justin King (businessman)|Justin King]], former CEO of [[Sainsbury's]].<ref name=\"bbc.co.uk1\"/>\n*[[Marc Bolland]], former CEO of [[Marks & Spencer]], former CEO of [[Morrisons]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/feb/22/brexit-eu-referendum-top-firms-sign-letter-times-pro-eu-shell-easyjet-bae-systems-supermarkets-sainsbury-morrisons-tesco|title=EU referendum: Top firms back pro-EU letter, but supermarkets refuse to sign|last1=Hellier|first1=David|last2=Inman|first2=Phillip|last3=Butler|first3=Sarah|date=22 February 2016|work=The Guardian}}</ref>\n*Sir [[Richard Branson]], entrepreneur, investor and philanthropist.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/sir-richard-branson-warns-leaving-eu-would-be-very-damaging-for-britain-a6883561.html|title=Sir Richard Branson warns leaving EU would be 'very damaging' for Britain|author=Heather Saul|date=19 February 2016|work=The Independent}}</ref>\n*[[Ian Davis (businessman)|Ian Davis]], chairman of [[Rolls-Royce Holdings]].<ref name=\"fteuwouldbeweakerft31may\"/>\n*[[Ant\u00f3nio Mota de Sousa Horta Os\u00f3rio|Ant\u00f3nio Horta-Os\u00f3rio]]; CEO of the [[Lloyds Banking Group]].<ref name=\"thepublicwantsft\"/>\n*Sir [[George Iacobescu]], CEO of the [[Canary Wharf Group]].<ref name=\"uncertaintyofbrexitjewishchronicle\"/>\n*[[Jamie Dimon]], chairman, president and chief executive officer of [[JPMorgan Chase]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-jpmorgan-dimon-brexit-idUKKCN0X32QJ|title=JPMorgan's Dimon warns of economic trouble from Brexit|agency=Reuters|publisher=Reueters|accessdate=6 April 2016|date=6 April 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Ian Livingston]], former CEO of the [[BT Group]].<ref name=\"uncertaintyofbrexitjewishchronicle\"/>\n*[[Alexander Asseily]], founder, Jawbone, State and Chiaro<ref name=\"Belfast Telegraph2016-04-20\" /><ref name=\"Stronger in Europe2016-04-20\" />\n*[[Alice Bentinck]], co-founder, Entrepreneur First<ref name=\"Belfast Telegraph2016-04-20\" /><ref name=\"Stronger in Europe2016-04-20\" />\n*Sir [[Victor Blank]], former chairman of [[Lloyds Bank]], philanthropist.<ref name=\"uncertaintyofbrexitjewishchronicle\">{{cite news|title=Uncertainty of Brexit would be bad for business, say leading fig