016-04-20\" /><ref name=\"Stronger in Europe2016-04-20\" />\n*Sir [[Nicholas Kenyon]], managing director of the [[Barbican Centre]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/goingout/exhibitions/sir-nicholas-kenyon-cutting-our-ties-with-the-eu-could-seriously-hurt-our-thriving-arts-scene-a3230506.html|title=Sir Nicholas Kenyon: 'Cutting our ties with the EU could seriously hurt our thriving arts scene'|work=London Evening Standard|date=21 April 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Robin Klein (venture capitalist)|Robin Klein]], co-founder, LocalGlobe<ref name=\"Belfast Telegraph2016-04-20\" /><ref name=\"Stronger in Europe2016-04-20\" />\n*[[Martha Lane Fox]], Baroness Lane-Fox CBE, founder of Doteveryone and co-founder of Lucky Voice and lastminute.com<ref name=\"Belfast Telegraph2016-04-20\">{{cite news | title = More than 200 entrepreneurs warn against 'hugely damaging' Brexit | newspaper = [[The Belfast Telegraph]] | date = 20 April 2016 | url = http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/news/uk/more-than-200-entrepreneurs-warn-against-hugely-damaging-brexit-34643104.html | access-date = 20 April 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Stronger in Europe2016-04-20\" />\n*[[Paul Lindley]], founder, Ella's Kitchen; and founder and CEO, Paddy's Bathroom<ref name=\"Belfast Telegraph2016-04-20\" /><ref name=\"Stronger in Europe2016-04-20\" />\n*[[Alastair Lukies]] CBE, Chairman, Innovate Finance<ref name=\"Belfast Telegraph2016-04-20\" /><ref name=\"Stronger in Europe2016-04-20\" />\n*[[Michael Richard Lynch|Mike Lynch]] OBE, Invoke Capital<ref name=\"Belfast Telegraph2016-04-20\" /><ref name=\"Stronger in Europe2016-04-20\" />\n*[[Carolyn McCall]], chief executive of [[easyjet]].<ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite web|url=http://blogs.spectator.co.uk/2015/10/britain-stronger-in-europe-launches-with-celebrities-and-a-dose-of-patriotism/|title='Britain Stronger in Europe' launches with celebrities and a dose of patriotism|date=12 October 2015|work=Coffee House}}</ref>\n*[[Deborah Meaden]], businesswoman and TV person