cretary]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sevenoaksforum.com/threads/sevenoaks-mp-michael-fallon-will-vote-to-stay-in-the-eu.6009/|title=Sevenoaks MP Michael Fallon will vote to STAY in the EU|work=Sevenoaks Forum|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160302103020/http://sevenoaksforum.com/threads/sevenoaks-mp-michael-fallon-will-vote-to-stay-in-the-eu.6009/|archivedate=2 March 2016}}</ref> \n* [[Sajid Javid]] ([[Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills|Business Secretary]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.spectator.co.uk/2016/02/spectator-exclusive-sajid-javid-backs-staying-in-the-eu/|title=Exclusive: Sajid Javid to back staying in the EU|work=Coffee House}}</ref> \n* [[Theresa May]] ([[Home Secretary]])<ref>{{cite news|last=Riley |first=Ben |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/theresa-may/12160472/Theresa-May-indicates-EU-is-vital-for-fight-against-terrorism-as-she-warns-against-isolation.html |title=Theresa May indicates EU is vital for fight against terrorism as she warns against 'isolation' |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |date=6 October 2015 |accessdate=19 February 2016}}</ref> \n* [[Patrick McLoughlin]] ([[Secretary of State for Transport|Transport Secretary]])<ref name=\"BBC News Tory MPs 2016\">{{cite web | title=EU Referendum: Where Conservative MPs stand | website=BBC News | date=20 February 2016 | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-eu-referendum-35616946 | accessdate=20 February 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Nicky Morgan]] ([[Secretary of State for Education|Education Secretary]])<ref name=\"BBC News Tory MPs 2016\" />\n* [[David Mundell]] ([[Secretary of State for Scotland]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/ng-interactive/2016/feb/20/eu-referendum-which-side-are-cabinet-ministers-on|title=EU referendum: which side are cabinet ministers on?|author=Rowena Mason|work=The Guardian}}</ref> \n* [[George Osborne]] ([[Chancellor of the Exchequer|Chancellor]])<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.u