 Enterprise]])<ref name=\"Conservatives In\"/>\n* [[Tina Stowell, Baroness Stowell of Beeston|Tina Stowell]] ([[Leader of the House of Lords]])<ref name=\"Conservatives In\"/>\n* [[Jeremy Wright]] ([[Attorney-General for England and Wales]] and [[Advocate General for Northern Ireland]])<ref name=\"Conservatives In\"/>\n}}\nOthers included former Prime Minister [[John Major]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/eureferendum/12053062/Sir-John-Major-isnt-alone-in-wanting-Britain-to-stay-in-the-EU-no-matter-what.html|title=Sir John Major isn't alone in wanting Britain to stay in the EU no matter what|author=Asa Bennett|date=16 December 2015|newspaper=The Telegraph|accessdate=17 December 2015}}</ref> former party leader [[William Hague]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/eureferendum/12064244/Why-I-will-be-voting-to-stay-in-Europe.html|title=Why I will be voting to stay in Europe|author=William Hague|date=23 December 2015|work=The Daily Telegraph|accessdate=23 December 2015}}</ref> former Deputy Prime Minister [[Michael Heseltine]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-35150356|title=EU referendum: Heseltine warns of Tory 'civil war'|date=21 December 2015|work=BBC News|accessdate=21 December 2015}}</ref> [[David Willetts]],<ref>{{cite news|author=Joe Murphy |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/politics/leaving-eu-would-cost-london-hundreds-of-millions-of-pounds-in-science-funding-a3144261.html |title=Leaving EU 'would cost London hundreds of millions of pounds' in science funding |newspaper=London Evening Standard |date=24 December 2015 |accessdate=24 December 2015}}</ref> former [[Chancellor of the Exchequer]] [[Kenneth Clarke|Ken Clarke]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-21272866|title=Ken Clarke: Leaving EU would be catastrophic|work=BBC News|accessdate=24 February 2016}}</ref> and former ministers [[Edwina Currie]]<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Edwina Currie, John Hilary, Tim Montgomerie, Leanne Wood |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b076prgv |access-date= 19 April 2016 |series=Any Questions? |series-link=Any Questions? |network=BBC |station=Radio 4}}</ref> and [[Baroness Warsi]] (who, it was alleged, supported Leave, despite the Vote Leave side not being aware of her support prior to the allegations).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-eu-referendum-36572894|title=EU referendum: Baroness Warsi switches from Leave to Remain|newspaper=BBC News|date=20 June 2016|accessdate=20 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://order-order.com/2016/06/20/warsi-wanted-europe-declined-join-leave-campaign/|title=Warsi 'Defection' Unravels|date=20 June 2016|accessdate=12 January 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe majority of the Conservative Party's 330 MPs announced that they would campaign for Britain to remain in the European Union. Including Cabinet Ministers, the list included:<ref name=\"Conservatives In\"/><ref name=\"Rowena Mason\">{{cite news|author=Rowena Mason |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/eureferendum/12202394/Why-this-lifelong-Eurosceptic-is-now-voting-to-stay-in.html |title=Why this lifelong Eurosceptic is now voting to stay in. |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |accessdate=24 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n{{columns-list|colwidth=22em|\n* [[Graham Stuart (politician)|Graham Stuart]] (Beverley and Holderness)\n* [[Amanda Milling]] (Cannock Chase)\n* [[Mel Stride]] (Central Devon)\n* [[Alex Chalk]] (Cheltenham)\n* [[Chris Philp]] (Croydon South)\n* [[Hugo Swire]] (East Devon)\n* [[Antoinette Sandbach]] (Eddisbury)\n* [[Maggie Throup]] (Erewash)\n* [[Angela Watkinson]] (Hornchurch and Upminster)\n* Sir [[Paul Beresford]] (Mole Valley)\n* [[Robert Jenrick]] (Newark)\n* [[David Mackintosh (politician)|David Mackintosh]] (Northampton South)\n* [[Rob Wilson]] (Reading East)\n* [[Lucy Frazer]] (South East Cambridgeshire)\n* [[Luke Hall (politician)|Luke Hall]] (Thornbury and Yate)\n* [[Tom Tugendhat]] (Tonbridge and Malling)\n* [[Tania Mathias]] (Twickenham)\n* [[Alun Cairns]] (Vale of Glamorgan)\n* [[David Mowat]] (Warrington South)\n* [[Graham Evans]] (Weaver Vale)\n* [[Steve Brine]] (Winchester)\n* [[Guto Bebb]] (Aberconwy)\n* [[Nick Herbert]] (Arundel and South Downs)\n* [[Damian Green]] (Ashford)\n* [[David Lidington]] (Aylesbury)\n* [[Victoria Prentis]] (Banbury)\n* [[Mark Lancaster]] (North East Milton Keynes)<ref name=MK>{{cite news|url=http://www.miltonkeynes.co.uk/news/local/tory-mps-split-over-vote-to-stay-in-the-european-union-1-7230216|title=Tory MPs split over vote to stay in the European Union|date=24 February 2016|newspaper=[[Milton Keynes Citizen]]|accessdate=26 February 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Maria Miller]] (Basingstoke)\n* [[Ben Howlett]] (Bath)\n* [[Jane Ellison]] (Battersea)\n* [[Dominic Grieve]] (Beaconsfield)\n* [[David Evennett]] (Bexleyheath and Crayford)\n* [[Paul Maynard]] (Blackpool North and Cleveleys)\n* [[Nick Gibb]] (Bognor Regis and Littlehampton)\n* [[Matt Warman]] (Boston and Skegness)\n* [[Tobias Ellwood]] (Bournemouth East)\n* [[Eric Pickles]] (Brentwood and Ongar)\n* [[Simon Kirby]] (Brighton Kemptown)\n* [[Keith Simpson (politician)|Keith Simpson]] (Broadland)\n* [[Bob Neill]] (Bromley and Chislehurt)\n* [[Sajid Javid]] (Bromsgrove)\n* [[Anna Soubry]] (Broxtowe)\n* [[Andrew Griffiths (politician)|Andrew Griffiths]] (Burton)\n* [[Jo Churchill]] (Bury St Edmunds)\n* [[Craig Whittaker]] (Calder Valley)\n* [[Craig Williams (politician)|Craig Williams]] (Cardiff North)\n* [[Simon Hart]] (Carmarthen West and South Pembrokeshire)\n* [[John Stevenson (British politician)|John Stevenson]] (Carlisle)\n* [[Dan Poulter]] (Central Suffolk and North Ipswich)\n* [[Edward Argar]] (Charnwood)\n* [[Simon Burns]] (Chelmsford)\n* [[Greg Hands]] (Chelsea and Fulham)\n* [[Michelle Donelan]] (Chippenham)\n* [[Mark Field]] (Cities of London and Westminster)\n* [[Edward Timpson]] (Crewe and Nantwich)\n* [[Gavin Barwell]] (Croydon Central)\n* [[Patrick McLoughlin]]