hard Benyon]] (Newbury)\n* [[Peter Heaton-Jones]] (North Devon)\n* [[Simon Hoare]] (North Dorset)\n* [[Alistair Burt]] (North East Bedfordshire)\n* [[Oliver Heald]] (North East Hertfordshire)\n* [[Michael Ellis (British politician)|Michael Ellis]] (Northampton North)\n* [[Roger Gale]] (North Thanet)\n* [[Shailesh Vara]] (North West Cambridgeshire)\n* [[Chloe Smith]] (Norwich North)\n* [[Marcus Jones (British politician)|Marcus Jones]] (Nuneaton)\n* [[James Brokenshire]] (Old Bexley and Sidcup)\n* [[Jo Johnson]] (Orpington)\n* [[Nicola Blackwood]] (Oxford West and Abingdon)\n* [[Rory Stewart]] (Penrith and The Border)\n* [[Oliver Colvile]] (Plymouth Sutton and Devonport)\n* [[Flick Drummond]] (Portsmouth South)\n* [[Stephen Crabb]] (Preseli Pembrokeshire)\n* [[Justine Greening]] (Putney)\n* [[Alok Sharma]] (Reading West)\n* [[Jake Berry]] (Rossendale and Darwen)\n* [[Mark Pawsey]] (Rugby)\n* [[Nick Hurd]] (Ruslip Northwood and Pinner)\n* [[Kenneth Clarke]] (Rushcliffe)\n* Sir [[Alan Duncan]] (Rutland and Melton)\n* [[Alan Haselhurst|Sir Alan Haselhurst]] (South Walden)\n* [[John Glen (politician)|John Glen]] (Salisbury)\n* [[Robert Goodwill]] (scarborough and Whitby)\n* [[Michael Fallon]] (Sevenoaks)\n* [[Mark Spencer (British politician)|Mark Spencer]] (Sherwood)\n* [[Julian Smith (politician)|Julian Smith]] (Skipton and Ripon)\n* [[Julian Knight (politician)|Julian Knight]] (Solihull)\n* [[Heidi Allen]] (South Cambridgeshire)\n* [[Alberto Costa (British politician)|Alberto Costa]] (South Leicestershire)\n* [[Gavin Williamson]] (South Staffordshire)\n* [[James Cartlidge]] (South Suffolk)\n* [[Robert Buckland]] (South Swindon)\n* [[Gary Streeter]] (South West Devon)\n* [[Philip Hammond]] (Runnymede and Weybridge)\n* [[Andrew Selous]] (South West Bedfordshire)\n* [[David Gauke]] (South West Hertfordshire)\n* [[Elizabeth Truss]] (South West Norfolk)\n* [[Jeremy Hunt]] (South West Surrey)\n* [[Therese Coffey]] (Suffolk Coastal)\n* [[Jeremy Lefroy]] (Stafford)\n* [[Karen Bradley]] (Staffordshire Moorlands)\n* [[Margot James]] (Stourbridge)\n* [[Neil Carmichael (Conservative politician)|Neil Carmichael]] (Stroud)\n* [[George Osborne]] (Tatton)\n* [[Rebecca Pow]] (Taunton Deane)\n* [[Sarah Wollaston|Dr.Sarah Wollaston]] (Totnes)<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/tory-mp-sarah-wollaston-switches-sides-in-eu-referendum-campaign_uk_57587e00e4b0415143693876?edition=uk&ir=UK&section=uk_uk|title=Tory MP Sarah Wollaston Switches Sides in EU Referendum Campaign|work=HuffPost}}</ref>\n* [[Mark Pritchard (politician)|Mark Pritchard]] (The Wrekin)\n* [[Kevin Hollinrake]] (Thrisk and Malton)\n* [[Neil Parish]] (Tiverton and Honiton)\n* [[Kevin Foster (politician)|Kevin Foster]] (Torbay)\n* [[Sarah Newton]] (Truro and Falmouth)\n* [[Greg Clark]] (Tunbridge Wells)\n* [[Ed Vaizey]] (Wantage)\n* [[Chris White (politician)|Chris White]] (Warwick and Leamington\n* [[Richard Harrington (politician)|Richard Harrington]] (Watford))\n* [[Peter Aldous]] (Waveney)\n* [[James Heappey]] (Wells)<ref>[http://www.conservativehome.com/platform/2016/06/james-heappey-the-eu-needs-major-change-but-leaving-isnt-worth-the-risk.htmlr ]{{dead link|date=July 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Grant Shapps]] (Welwyn Hatfield)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.shapps.com/2016/06/the-rt-hon-grant-shapps-mp-statement-on-eu-referendum/|title=The Rt Hon Grant Shapps MP statement on EU Referendum|author=Grant Shapps|website=The Rt Hon Grant Shapps MP|date=9 June 2016|accessdate=9 June 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160609145933/http://www.shapps.com/2016/06/the-rt-hon-grant-shapps-mp-statement-on-eu-referendum/|archivedate=9 June 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Oliver Letwin]] (West Dorset)\n* [[Matthew Hancock]] (West Suffolk)\n* [[Harriett Baldwin]] (West Worcestershire)\n* [[John Penrose]] (Weston-Super-Mare)\n* [[Stephen Hammond]] (Wimbledon)\n* [[David Cameron]] (Witney)\n* [[Robin Walker]] (Worcester)\n* [[Peter Bottomley]] (Worthing West)\n* [[Ben Wallace (politician)|Ben Wallace]] (Wyre and Preston North)\n* [[Mark Garnier]] (Wyre Forest)\n}}\n\nThe list of Conservative [[Members of the European Parliament]] (MEPs) that announced that they would campaign for Britain to remain in the European Union is:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.conservatives.in/meps|title=Members of the European Parliament|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160518101504/http://www.conservatives.in/meps|archivedate=18 May 2016}}</ref>\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n* [[Richard Ashworth]] (South East England)\n* [[Daniel Dalton (British politician)|Daniel Dalton]] (West Midlands)\n* [[Vicky Ford]]<ref>{{cite web|title=How I will be voting in the up coming UK referendum and why|url=http://vickyford.org/communications/latest-news/how-i-will-be-voting-in-the-up-coming-uk-referendum/752|website=vickyford.org|accessdate=31 March 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160404133837/http://vickyford.org/communications/latest-news/how-i-will-be-voting-in-the-up-coming-uk-referendum/752|archive-date=4 April 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> (East of England)\n* [[Jacqueline Foster]] (North West England)\n* [[Ashley Fox]] (South West England)\n* [[Julie Girling]] (South West England)\n* [[Sajjad Karim]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Sajjad backs Britain Stronger in Europe campaign|url=http://www.sajjadkarim.eu/campaigns/sajjad-backs-britain-stronger-europe-campaign|website=sajjadkarim.eu|accessdate=31 March 2016}}</ref> (North West England)\n* [[Timothy Kirkhope]] (Yorkshire and the Humber)\n* [[Anthea McIntyre]] (West Midlands)\n* [[Kay Swinburne]] (Wales)\n* [[Charles Tannock]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Most Tories want to remain in the EU. Here's why|url=http://blogs.spectator.co.uk/2015/06/most-tories-want-to-remain-in-the-eu-heres-why/|website=Spectator Blogs|accessdate=31 March 2016}}</ref> (London)\n}}\n\nOther Conservatives supporting a Remain vote were:\n* [[Stephen Greenhalgh]], the Deputy London Mayor until May 2016.<ref>{{cite we