o.uk/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-36383590|title=EU referendum debate: MSPs vote overwhelmingly for UK to remain in EU|work=BBC News|date=26 May 2016|publisher=The British Broadcasting Corporation}}</ref>\n\n====Independent====\n* [[Sylvia Hermon]] (MP for [[North Down (UK Parliament constituency)|North Down]]);<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-northern-ireland-35529573|title=DUP motion on timing of EU referendum defeated|newspaper=BBC News|date=9 February 2016|accessdate=26 February 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Jeffrey Evans, 4th Baron Mountevans]], Lord Mayor of London.<ref name=\"cityamlordmayor\">{{cite news|last1=Fedor|first1=Lauren|title=EU referendum: Lord Mayor Jeffrey Mountevans says Britain is better off in the European Union ahead of controversial City of London Corporation vote|url=http://www.cityam.com/235856/eu-referendum-lord-mayor-jeffrey-mountevans-says-britain-is-better-off-in-the-european-union-ahead-of-controversial-city-of-london-corporation-vote|accessdate=4 March 2016|work=City A.M.|date=2 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n===International figures===\n\n==== From other European Union member states ====\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n*[[Magdalena Andersson (Social Democrat)|Magdalena Andersson]], Minister of Finance of Sweden<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.government.se/opinion-pieces/2016/02/sweden-wants-the-uk-to-remain-in-the-eu/ |title=Sweden wants the UK to remain in the EU |website=Government.se |date=17 February 2016 |accessdate=2 March 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Silvio Berlusconi]], former [[Prime Minister of Italy]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/politica/berlusconi-l-europa-deve-andare-avanti-mi-preoccupano-movimenti-anti-ue-come-quello-di-le-pen-_3009756-201602a.shtml|title=Berlusconi: \"L'Europa deve andare avanti, mi preoccupano movimenti anti-Ue come quello di Le Pen\"|date=20 May 2016}}</ref>\n*[[John Bruton]], former [[Taoiseach|Prime Minister of Republic of Ireland]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/business/economy/uk-will-lose-influence-on-global-economy-if-it-leaves-eu-bruton-1.2628421|title=UK will lose influence on global economy if it leaves EU \u2013 Bruton|newspaper=The Irish Times |accessdate=29 April 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Mario Draghi]], [[President of the European Central Bank]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2016-04-27/draghi-tells-germany-criticism-may-slow-return-to-higher-rates |title=Draghi Tells Germany Criticism May Slow Return to Higher Rates |publisher=Bloomberg L.P.|accessdate=29 April 2016}}</ref>\n*Euripides Evriviades, High Commissioner to the UK of Cyprus<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.embassymagazine.com/biog/biog_countries/biog_emb52_cyprus.html |work= Embassy Magazine|title=Full-throttle diplomacy|accessdate=29 March 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Charles Flanagan]], [[Minister for Foreign Affairs and Trade]] of the Republic of Ireland<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/politics/irish-in-britain-should-oppose-brexit-minister-says-1.2599661|title=Irish in Britain should oppose Brexit, Foreign Minister says  |newspaper=The Irish Times |accessdate=6 April 2016 }}</ref>\n*[[Rebecca Harms]] MEP, co-chair of [[The Greens\u2013European Free Alliance]].<ref name=\"UKinEU\"/>\n*[[Fran\u00e7ois Hollande]], [[President of France]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.news.com.au/world/europe/british-pm-david-cameron-goes-headtohead-with-european-union-leaders-atbrussels-summit/news-story/4ec49ee5743f16935aa26f48fee503ed |title=David Cameron, British Prime Minister, on European Union negotiations |website=News.com.au |date=19 February 2016 |accessdate=2 March 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Klaus Iohannis]], President of Romania<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.romaniajournal.ro/president-iohannis-uk-must-stay-in-the-eu-but-we-wont-accept-discrimination-against-romanians/|title=President Iohannis: UK must stay in the EU, but we won't accept discrimination against Romanians \u2013 The Romania Journal|date=18 February 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Enda Kenny]], [[T