mans]], artist & photographer. Winner of the [[Turner Prize#2000|2000 Turner Prize]]<ref>{{cite web|title=EU Campaign|url=http://tillmans.co.uk/campaign-eu|website=Wolfgang Tillmans|accessdate=27 April 2016}}</ref> \n*[[Helen Tse]], author and chef<ref name=\"auto5\"/>\n*[[Steve Turner (trade unionist)|Steve Turner]], trade unionist<ref name=\"theguardian.com\"/>\n*[[Bj\u00f6rn Ulvaeus]], musical producer, singer & song-writer<ref>{{cite web|title=Abba's Bj\u00f6rn Ulvaeus on UK's European Union referendum|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-eu-referendum-36286255|website=BBC News|accessdate=13 May 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Manjinder Virk]], actress and filmmaker<ref name=\"auto5\"/>\n*[[Hibo Wardere]], anti-female genital mutilation campaigner<ref name=\"auto5\"/>\n*[[Robert Webb]], comedian, actor, and writer<ref>{{cite tweet|user=arobertwebb|author=Robert Webb|number=745376081390211072|date=21 June 2016|title=But I wouldn't risk Leave \u2013 I wouldn't risk other people's jobs.  That's it for me. You don't fuck around with other people's jobs. The end.|accessdate=23 June 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Justin Welby]], [[Archbishop of Canterbury]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailyecho.co.uk/news/national/14551850.Archbishop_of_Canterbury_will_vote_to_stay_in_EU/?commentSort=score|title=Archbishop of Canterbury will vote to stay in EU|accessdate=23 June 2016}}</ref>\n*Sir [[Simon Wessely]], president of the [[Royal College of Psychiatrists]]<ref name=\"Healthier In\"/>\n*[[Zoe Williams]], journalist and writer<ref name=\"theguardian.com\"/>\n*[[Robert Winston]], Baron Winston, scientist<ref name=\"lordrobertwinstonwarnsof\">{{cite news|last1=Meechan|first1=Brian|title=Lord Robert Winston warns of Brexit 'disaster' for universities|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-wales-35696512|accessdate=1 March 2016|work=BBC News|date=1 March 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Florence Welch]] \u2013 lead singer [[Florence + The Machine]]\n*[[John Lydon]] (Johnny Rotten) \u2013 singer, [[Sex Pistols]] and [[Public Image Ltd.]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://metro.co.uk/2016/04/22/exclusive-john-lydon-talks-pil-punk-and-donald-trump-5795582/|title=Exclusive: John Lydon talks PiL, Punk, and Donald Trump|date=22 April 2016|accessdate=25 June 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Paul Cook]] \u2013 drummer, [[Sex Pistols]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.spectator.co.uk/2016/03/anarchy-in-the-eu-the-sex-pistols-drummer-on-why-brexit-isnt-punk/|title=Anarchy in the EU: the Sex Pistols' drummer on why Brexit isn't punk|accessdate=25 June 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n\n====Healthcare professionals letter====\nIn a letter to ''The Times'', around 200 healthcare professionals defended the EU as an overall benefit to UK public health, the NHS and health research. Sections from the letter stated \"As health professionals and researchers we write to highlight the valuable benefits of continued EU membership to the NHS, medical innovation and UK public health\". \"We have made enormous progress over decades in international health research, health services innovation and public health. Much has been built around shared policies and capacity across the EU\". \"EU trade deals will not privatise the NHS as the EU negotiating position now contains clear safeguards. Decisions on NHS privatisation are in UK government hands alone. EU immigration is a net benefit to our NHS in terms of finances, staffing and exchanges\". \"Finally, leaving the EU would not provide a financial windfall for the NHS\". Signatories included:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://healthierin.eu/2016/04/health-pros-publish-pro-eu-letter-in-the-times/|title=Health pros publish pro-EU letter in The Times \u2013 Healthier in the EU|date=4 April 2016|access-date=4 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160404142508/http://healthierin.eu/2016/04/health-pros-publish-pro-eu-letter-in-the-times/|archive-date=4 April 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/leaving-eu-would-put-nhs-at-risk-health-professionals-warn-zdrq7r2hm|title=Brexit would put the NHS at risk, health leaders warn}}</ref>\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n* Baroness [[Elaine Murphy, Baroness Murphy|Elaine Murphy]] FRCPsych, Professor of Psychiatry, London\n* Baroness [[Sheila Hollins]], former President Royal College of Psychiatrists, London\n* [[Lord Alderdice]] FRCPsych, Senior Research Fellow, Harris Manchester College, University of Oxford, Oxford\n* Lord [[Ara Darzi]] OM, Paul Hamlyn Professor of Surgery, Imperial College\n* Lord [[Nigel Crisp]], former Chief Executive NHS, London\n* Professor Dame [[Janet Thornton]], Senior Scientist, European Bioinformatics Institute European Molecular Biology Laboratory\n* Professor Dame [[Jill Macleod Clark]], Professor of Nursing, University of Southampton\n* Professor Dame [[Til Wykes]], Professor and Vice Dean, King's College London\n* Dame [[Sue Bailey]], Past President, Royal College of Psychiatrists\n* Sir [[Andrew Haines|Andy Haines]], former Dean, London School of Hygiene & Tropical Medicine\n* Sir [[Cyril Chantler]], formerly Chairman of The King's Fund and the UCL Partners academic health science network, London\n* Sir [[David Nicholson (civil servant)|David Nicholson]], former Chief Executive NHS\n* Sir [[Eric Thomas (gynaecologist)|Eric Thomas]], former Vice-Chancellor, University of Bristol\n* Sir [[George Alberti]], Visiting Professor, King's College, London\n* Sir [[Harry Burns (doctor)|Harry Burns]], Professor of Global Public Health, University of Strathclyde\n* Sir [[Iain Chalmers]], Coordinator, James Lind Initiative, Oxford\n* Sir [[Ian Gilmore]], professor, University of Liverpool\n* Sir [[Keith Peters (physician)|Keith Peters]], Emeritus Regius Professor of Physic University of Cambridge, President of Academy of Medical Sciences 2002\u20132006, Cambridge\n* Sir [[Norman Stanley Williams|Norman Williams]], former President, Royal College of Surgeons\n* Sir [[Richard Thompson (physician)|Richard Thompson]], Immediate past-president, Royal College of