and\n*[[Pawel Pawlikowski]], director\n*[[Peter Florence]] MBE, director, Hay Festival\n*[[Peter Morgan]], writer\n*Peter Rice, sound design\n*[[Peter Strickland (director)|Peter Strickland]], director\n*[[Philip Pullman]], writer\n*[[Piers Aggett]] (Rudimental), musician\n*[[Polly Stenham]], writer\n*Professor [[Eyal Weizman]], architect and Professor of Spatial and Visual Cultures at Goldsmiths, University of London, and director of the Centre for Research Architecture\n*Professor [[Jonathan Shalit]] OBE, Chairman, ROAR Group\n*[[Rhodri Meilir]], actor\n*[[Richard Curtis]], writer and director\n*[[Richard Rogers]], architect\n*[[Richard Wentworth (artist)|Richard Wentworth]], artist\n*[[Robert Montgomery (artist)|Robert Montgomery]], artist and poet\n*[[Ron Arad (industrial designer)|Ron Arad]], designer\n*[[Sabrina Guinness]], producer\n*[[Sally Wainwright]], writer, director and Executive Producer\n*[[Sam Taylor-Johnson]] OBE, filmmaker, artist\n*[[Sam Thorne]], director, Nottingham Contemporary\n*[[Samuel West]], actor\n*[[Sandi Toksvig]] OBE, founder of the Women's Equality Party, author, comedian and presenter\n*Dr. [[Sandie Shaw]], Chair, Featured Artist Coalition\n*[[Sara and Leonie Lowri]], The Eggs Collective\n*[[Sarah Solemani]], actress and writer\n*[[Saul Dibb]], director\n*[[Shirazeh Houshiary]], artist\n*[[Simon Patterson (artist)|Simon Patterson]], artist\n*[[Simon Stephens]], writer\n*Sir [[Anish Kapoor]], sculptor\n*Sir [[David Chipperfield]] CBE, RA RDI RIBA architect\n*Sir [[Derek Jacobi]] CBE, actor\n*Sir [[John Hurt]] CBE, actor\n*Sir [[John Sorrell (designer)|John Sorrell]] CBE, Chairman of Creative Industries Federation\n*Sir [[Matthew Bourne]], Artistic Director, New Adventures\n*Sir [[Patrick Stewart]], actor and activist\n*Sir [[Tom Stoppard]] OM CBE, playwright and screenwriter\n*[[Sonia Friedman]], producer\n*[[Sophie Fiennes]], director, producer\n*[[Sophie Okonedo]], actor\n*[[Stephen Daldry]] CBE, director and producer\n*[[Stephen Frears]], director\n*[[Stephen Woolley]], producer, director\n*[[Steve Coogan]], actor, producer, writer\n*[[Steve McQueen (director)|Steve McQueen]], director\n*[[Tacita Dean]], artist\n*[[Thandie Newton]], actress\n*[[Thea Sharrock]], director\n*[[Thomas Heatherwick]], designer\n*[[Tim Bevan]], co-chairman, Working Title Films\n*[[Tim Pigott-Smith]], actor, director, writer\n*[[Tom Geens]], director\n*[[Tom Harper (director)|Tom Harper]], director\n*[[Tom Hooper]], director\n*[[Tony Bevan]], artist\n*[[Tracey Emin]], artist\n*[[Tracey Seaward]], producer\n*[[Vicky Featherstone]], Artistic Director of the Royal Court Theatre, London\n*[[Wayne McGregor]] CBE, Choreographer and founder of Studio Wayne McGregor\n*[[Wolfgang Tillmans]] RA Artist\n*[[Yana Peel]], CEO of the Serpentine Galleries\n}}\n\n==== Economists' letter ====\nIn a letter to ''The Times'', 279 economists stated that Brexit would \"entail significant long-term costs\". The signatories wrote, \"focusing entirely on the economics, we consider that it would be a major mistake for the UK to leave the European Union.\" At the time of publication the letter had 199 signatories. A further 80 signed after publication.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/economists-warn-against-brexit-vote-bh07fdx0t|title=Economists warn against Brexit vote|website=The Times|access-date=24 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cep.lse.ac.uk/textonly/_new2014/BREXIT/BREXIT_LETTER_23May2016.pdf|title=The letter: [published in The Times, 11.05.16]|website=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://longandvariable.wordpress.com/2016/05/23/280-economists-now-against-brexit-as-ucl-and-lse-sign/|title=280 economists now against Brexit as UCL and LSE sign|first=Tony|last=Yates|date=23 May 2016}}</ref>\n\n==== Lawyers' report ====\nAround 300 lawyers signed a report on UK membership of the EU and the alternatives. They stated: \"we recognised how much of the debate on the UK's membership of the EU is based on a lack of information, misconceptions, or, worse, misinformation [...] Ultimately, we believe a sensible judgment on EU membership can be made only on the basis of reliable evidence\". The signatories \"consider that the UK's interests are best served by remaining in the EU\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lawyers-inforbritain.uk/signatories/|title=Signatories|date=29 February 2016}}</ref>\n\n==== Historians letter ====\nIn a letter to the Guardian, more than 300 prominent historians urged the United Kingdom to remain in the European Union. The letter said, \"On 23 June, we face a choice: to cast ourselves adrift, condemning ourselves to irrelevance and Europe to division and weakness; or to reaffirm our commitment to the EU and stiffen the cohesion of our continent in a dangerous world.\" Notable signatories included:<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/may/24/lessons-from-history-for-the-brexiteers|title=Lessons from history for the Brexiteers {{!}} Letters from Simon Schama and others and Jack Dromey MP|last=Letters|date=24 May 2016|website=The Guardian|access-date=25 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/may/25/vote-to-leave-eu-will-condemn-britain-to-irrelevance-say-historians|title=Vote to leave EU would 'condemn Britain to irrelevance', say historians|last=Stewart|first=Heather|date=25 May 2016|website=The Guardian|access-date=25 May 2016}}</ref>\n{{columns-list|colwidth=18em|\n*Professor [[Simon Schama]]\n*Professor [[Ian Kershaw]]\n*Professor [[Niall Ferguson]]\n*Dr [[Juliet Gardiner]]\n*[[D. R. Thorpe]]\n*Professor [[David Runciman]]\n*[[Richard Davenport-Hines]]\n*Professor [[Colin Jones (historian)|Colin Jones]]\n*Professor [[Michael Burleigh]]\n*Professor [[R. F. Foster (historian)|Roy Foster]]\n*Dr [[Marc Morris]]\n*Dr [[Suzannah Lipscomb]]\n*Professor [[Ali Ansari]]\n*[[Robert Lacey]]\n*Professor [[Richard Overy]]\n*Professor [[Beatrice Heuser]]\n*Professor [[Richard Bessel]]\n*Professor [[Patricia Clavin]]\n*Professor [[Dominic Lieven]]\n*Professor [[Keith Thomas (historian)|Keith Thomas]]\n}}\n\n====Armed Forces and Security Services====\n* [[Jonathan Evans, Baron Evans of Weardale|Sir Jonathan Evans]], former [[Director General of MI5]]<ref name=\"The Sunday Times\">{{cite news|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/edition/news/spy-chiefs-say-quitting-eu-is-security-risk-fgzgpgkgk|title=Spy chiefs say quitting EU is security risk|newspaper=The Sunday Times|date=8 May 2016|accessdate=8 May 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Eliza Manningham-Buller]], former [[Director General of MI5]]<ref name=\"The Guardian\">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/may/11/britain-less-safe-outside-eu-former-mi5-chief-eliza-manningham-buller|title='Britain less safe outside EU', says former M15 Chief Eliza Manningham Buller|newspaper=The Guardian|date=11 May 2016|accessdate=11 May 2016}}</ref>\n* [[John Sawers|Sir John Sawers]], former [[Chief of the Secret Intelligence Service]] ([[Secret Intelligence Service|MI6]])<ref name=\"The Sunday Times\"/>\n* Sir [[Hugh Orde]], former president of the [[Association of Chief Police Officers]], and former Chief Constable of the [[Police Service of Northern Ireland]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=Watt|first1=Nicholas|title=EU exit would make UK a magnet for fugitives, warns former Acpo chief|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/oct/12/eu-referendum-uk-exit-safe-haven-fugitives-hugh-orde-acpo|accessdate=23 March 2016|work=The Guardian}}</ref>\n* [[Lynne Owens]], [[Director-General of the National Crime Agency]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.sky.com/story/1677285/warning-over-crime-risk-if-uk-leaves-eu|title=Warning Over Crime Risk If UK Leaves EU|publisher=Sky News}}</ref>\n* [[Richard Dannatt|General Lord Dannatt]], former [[Chief of the General Staff]]<ref name=\"autogenerated2\">{{cite news|title=UK safer inside EU, former defence chiefs say|work=BBC News|date=24 February 2016|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-eu-referendum-35647071|accessdate=9 June 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Rupert Smith|General Sir Rupert Smith]], former [[Deputy Supreme Allied Commander Europe]]<ref name=\"autogenerated2\"/>\n* [[John Kiszely|Lieutenant General Sir John Kiszeley]], former [[Deputy Supreme Allied Commander Europe]]<ref name=\"autogenerated2\"/>\n* [[Mark Stanhope|Admiral Sir Mark Stanhope]], former [[First Sea Lord]]<ref name=\"autogenerated2\"/>\n* [[Jock Stirrup|Lord Stirrup]], Marshal of the [[Royal Air Force]], former [[Chief of the Defence Staff (United Kingdom)|Chief of Defence Staff]]<ref name=\"autogenerated2\"/>\n* [[Rob Wainwright (civil servant)|Robert Wainwright]], director of [[Europol]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Nigel Farage quotes head of Europol, gets contradicted by head of Europol|url=http://leftfootforward.org/2016/05/nigel-farage-quotes-head-of-europol-gets-contradicted-by-head-of-europol/|website=LeftFootForward|date=17 May 2016|accessdate=17 May 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Lieutenant-General]] [[Richard Shirreff|Sir Richard Shirreff]], former [[Deputy Supreme Allied Commander Europe|Deputy Supreme Allied Commander of NATO]]<ref>{{cite news |date=27 February 2016 |url= https://www.wsws.org/en/articles/2016/02/27/mili-f27.html|title=UK generals intervene to oppose Brexit |accessdate=20 May 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Peter Carington, 6th Baron Carrington]], former [[Secretary General of NATO]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/opinion/2016/05/09/letters-at-a-time-of-global-instability-britain-needs-to-stand-u/|title=Letters: At a time of global instability, Britain needs to stand united with its EU allies|newspaper=The Telegraph|date=10 May 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Edwin Bramall|Field Marshal Edwin Bramall, Baron Bramall]], former [[Chief of the Defence Staff (United Kingdom)|Chief of Defence Staff]], [[British Army]]<ref name=\"telegraph.co.uk2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/eureferendum/12170890/Britain-must-stay-in-the-EU-to-protect-itself-from-Isil-former-military-chiefs-say.html|title=Britain must stay in the EU to protect itself from Isil, former military chiefs say|date=23 February 2016|last1=Dominiczak|first1=Peter}}</ref>\n* [[Michael Boyce, Baron Boyce|Admiral of the Fleet Michael Boyce, Baron Boyce]], former [[Chief of the Defence Staff (United Kingdom)|Chief of Defence Staff]], [[Royal Navy]]<ref name=\"telegraph.co.uk2\"/>\n* General Sir [[Mike Jackson (British Army officer)|Mike Jackson]], former [[Chief of the General Staff (United Kingdom)|Chief of the General Staff]], [[British Army]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.express.co.uk/news/uk/653983/Gen-Sir-Mike-Jackson-furious-anti-Europe-campaign-group|title=Gen Sir Mike Jackson furious with anti-Europe campaign group|author= Marco Giannangeli|newspaper=Daily Express|date=20 March 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Robert Fry|Lieutenant General Sir Rob Fry]], former Deputy Chief of Defence Staff, [[Royal Marines]]<ref name=\"telegraph.co.uk2\"/>\n* [[Jonathan Shaw (British Army officer)|Jonathan Shaw]], Major-General, [[British Army]].{{citation needed|date=April 2018}}\n\n====Letters to The Guardian by European writers====\nOn 4 June 2016, ''The Guardian'' newspaper published a number of 'letters to Britain' by European (non-British) writers and intellectuals giving their opinion on the referendum and Britain's place in Europe. All of the letters expressed support for remain.<ref>{{cite news|title=Dear Britain: Elena Ferrante, Slavoj \u017di\u017eek and other European writers on Brexit|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/jun/04/dear-britain-letters-from-europe-referendum|accessdate=5 June 2016|newspaper=The Guardian|date=4 June 2016}}</ref> The writers were:\n* [[Elena Ferrante]], Italian\n* [[Javier Marias]], Spanish\n* [[Timur Vermes]], German\n* [[Anne Enright]], Irish\n* [[Yanis Varoufakis]], Greek\n* [[Riad Sattouf]], French\n* [[Jonas Jonasson]], Swedish \n* [[Kapka Kassabova]], Bulgarian\n* [[Slavoj Zizek]], Slovenian\n\n====Nobel Prize laureates letter====\nOn 10 June 2016, ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'' published a letter signed by 13 winners of the Nobel Prize expressing the view that being part of the EU is good for British science and that is good for Britain.<ref>{{cite news | title = Letters | newspaper = [[The Daily Telegraph]] | date = 10 June 2016 | url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/opinion/2016/06/10/letters-eu-campaigners-have-lost-support-by-shouting-and-persona/ | access-date = 11 June 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Sydney Brenner|Dr Sydney Brenner]], Laureate, Physiology or Medicine 2002\n* [[Martin Evans|Sir Martin Evans]], Laureate, Physiology or Medicine 2007\n* [[Andre Geim|Sir Andre Geim]], Laureate, Physics 2010\n* [[John Gurdon|Sir John Gurdon]], Laureate, Physiology or Medicine 2012\n* [[Peter Higgs|Professor Peter Higgs]], Laureate, Physics 2013\n* [[Tim Hunt|Sir Tim Hunt]], Laureate, Physiology or Medicine 2001\n* [[Tomas Lindahl|Dr Tomas Lindahl]], Laureate, Chemistry 2015\n* [[Konstantin Novoselov|Sir Kostya Novoselov]], Laureate, Physics 2010\n* [[Paul Nurse|Sir Paul Nurse]], Laureate, Physiology or Medicine 2001\n* [[John O'Keefe (neuroscientist)|Professor John O'Keefe]], Laureate, Physiology or Medicine 2014\n* [[Richard J. Roberts|Sir Richard Roberts]], Laureate, Physiology or Medicine 1993\n* [[John Sulston|Sir John Sulston]], Laureate, Physiology or Medicine 2002\n* [[John E. Walker|Sir John Walker]], Laureate, Chemistry 1997\n\n====Nobel Prize in Economics laureates letter====\nOn 19 June 2016, ''[[The Guardian]]'' published a letter signed by 10 winners of the [[Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences]], expressing the view that the \"economic argument\" was clearly in favour of continued UK membership within the EU.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/jun/19/we-nobel-prize-winning-economists-believe-the-uk-is-better-off-in-the-eu|title=We Nobel prize-winning economists believe the UK is better off in the EU \u2013 Letters|last=Letters|date=19 June 2016|accessdate=23 June 2016}}</ref>