ate-lost-no-matter-who-wins |title=The EU Debate Is Lost No Matter Who Wins |publisher=Liberty GB |date=21 February 2016 |accessdate=3 March 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306145330/http://libertygb.org.uk/news/eu-debate-lost-no-matter-who-wins |archive-date=6 March 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[New Communist Party of Britain]]<ref name=\"leaflet\">{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/04/12/conservative-donors-prepare-to-sink-5million-into-brexit-campaig/|title=Conservative donors prepare to sink \u00a35million into Brexit campaign amid anger about pro-EU leaflet|author=Christopher Hope and Peter Dominiczak|date=12 April 2016|newspaper=The Daily Telegraph|accessdate=6 May 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Communist Party of Britain (Marxist\u2013Leninist)]]\n*[[Libertarian Party (UK)]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://libertarianpartyuk.com/referendum-2016/ |title=REFERENDUM 2016 |publisher=Libertarian party UK |date=17 June 2016 |accessdate=10 May 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180924164716/https://libertarianpartyuk.com/referendum-2016/ |archive-date=24 September 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[Communist Party of Britain]]\n*[[Communist Party of Great Britain (Marxist\u2013Leninist)]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cpgb-ml.org/2016/04/01/news/world/europe/why-british-workers-need-a-brexit/|title=Why British workers need a Brexit|work=CPGB-ML|access-date=27 July 2018}}</ref>\n* [[National Front (UK)]]\n* [[Respect Party]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.respectparty.org/2016/02/22/respect-to-campaign-to-leave-the-european-union/|title=Respect to campaign to leave the EU|work=The Respect Party|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303080320/http://www.respectparty.org/2016/02/22/respect-to-campaign-to-leave-the-european-union/|archivedate=3 March 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Revolutionary Communist Party of Britain (Marxist\u2013Leninist)]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rcpbml.org.uk/wwie-16/ww16_special_edition_eu.htm|title=Workers' Weekly Internet Edition Year 2016 Volume 46 Number|website=rcpbml.org.uk|access-date=27 July 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Social Democratic Party (UK, 1990\u2013present)|Social Democratic Party (SDP)]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.socialdemocraticparty.co.uk/|title=Home|accessdate=23 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150509052819/http://www.socialdemocraticparty.co.uk/sdp-principles.php|archive-date=9 May 2015|url-status=dead}}{{better source|date=June 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Socialist Labour Party (UK)|Socialist Labour Party]]<ref>Socialist Labour Party: [http://www.socialist-labour-party.org.uk/electioncampaign.html The EU Referendum]</ref>\n* [[Trade Unionist and Socialist Coalition]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tusc.org.uk/17182/22-02-2016/tusc-letter-in-the-guardian-now-sign-the-petition |title=Tusc Letter in the Guardian Now Sign The Petition |website=Tusc.org.uk |date=22 February 2016 |accessdate=2 March 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304173007/https://www.tusc.org.uk/17182/22-02-2016/tusc-letter-in-the-guardian-now-sign-the-petition |archivedate=4 March 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://search.electoralcommission.org.uk/English/Registrations/PerPar3955|title=View registration \u2013 The Electoral Commission}}</ref>\n* [[UK Independence Party]] (UKIP)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ukip.org/|title=UK Independence Party |work=UKIP}}</ref>\n* [[The Justice & Anti-Corruption Party]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jacparty.org.uk/|title=The Justice & Anti-Corruption Party|website=jacparty.org.uk}}</ref>\n*[[Workers Revolutionary Party (UK)|Workers Revolutionary Party]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wrp.org.uk/news/12211|title=Workers Revolutionary Party \u2013 VOTE LEAVE BRING DOWN CAMERON FORWARD TO SOCIALIST UNITED STATES OF EUROPE!|last=Party|first=Workers Revolutionary|website=wrp.org.uk|date=22 June 2016|access-date=27 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n'''Parties in England:'''\n\n* [[English Democrats]]<ref>