exit/|title=Labour MSP breaks ranks to make 'left-wing' case for Brexit|author=Aiden Kerr|publisher=STV|date=26 May 2016|accessdate=27 May 2016}}</ref>\n\nFormer Labour MPs:\n* [[Tom Harris (British politician)|Tom Harris]] ([[Glasgow South (UK Parliament constituency)|Glasgow South]] (2001\u20132015)<ref name=\"autogenerated4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-35841224|title=EU referendum: Tom Harris to head Scottish Vote Leave campaign|work=BBC News|accessdate=19 March 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Ian Davidson (British politician)|Ian Davidson]] ([[Glasgow South West (UK Parliament constituency)|Glasgow South West]] (1992\u20132015)<ref name=\"autogenerated4\"/>\n* [[Austin Mitchell]] ([[Great Grimsby (UK Parliament constituency)|Great Grimsby]] (1977\u20132015)<ref name=\"labourleave1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.labourleave.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/The-Labour-Case-for-Brexit.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=10 June 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614212515/http://www.labourleave.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/The-Labour-Case-for-Brexit.pdf |archivedate=14 June 2016 }}</ref>\n* [[Nigel Griffiths]] ([[Edinburgh South (UK Parliament constituency)|Edinburgh South]] 1987\u20132010)<ref name=\"autogenerated4\"/>\n\n====Green Party====\nWithin the [[Green Party of England and Wales|Green Party]] (which supported Remain): the Green Leaves organisation campaigned on behalf of Green Party members who advocated a leave vote.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://green-leaves.org/|title=Home}}</ref> Member of the House of Lords and former London Assembly Member [[Jenny Jones, Baroness Jones of Moulsecoomb|Jenny Jones]] (Baroness Jones) campaigned to leave.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2015/10/09/european-referendum-vote-leave-campaign-launched-political-donors_n_8267464.html|title=European Referendum: Vote Leave Campaign Launched, Bankrolled By Three of Britain's Biggest Political Donors|work