politician)|Alex Neil]] declared that he has voted leave and that several of his fellow SNP MSPs did likewise.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.heraldscotland.com/news/14843960.Alex_Neil__I_voted_for_Brexit_and_I_was_not_the_only_SNP_MSP_who_backed_leave/|title=Alex Neil: I voted for Brexit and I was not the only SNP MSP who backed leave|website=The Herald|location=Glasgow}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-37870167|title=SNP ex-minister Alex Neil voted for Brexit|date=4 November 2016|via=bbc.com}}</ref> There are multiple groups for SNP members advocating a leave vote, such as ''SNP Vote Leave'' and ''SNP GO!''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.express.co.uk/news/uk/675954/Scotland-SNP-Nicola-Sturgeon-EU-vote-Remain-out-UK-Dundee|title=New blow for Sturgeon's fight to stay in EU as SNP activists launch new Out drive|date=31 May 2016|accessdate=23 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n====Ulster Unionist Party====\nWithin the [[Ulster Unionist Party|UUP]] (which supports Remain): [[Harold McKee]] MLA<ref>{{cite tweet|user=NIVote_Leave|author=NI Vote Leave|number=739128591053664256|date=4 June 2016|title=Thanks to Harold McKee MLA, @ccmccuup, @alexredpath1989, Cllr Dudgeon et al joining .@DanHannanMEP at final NI event|accessdate=23 June 2016}}</ref> and former leader [[Tom Elliott (politician)|Tom Elliot]] MP<ref>{{cite tweet|user=AlexKane221b|author=Alex.Kane|number=743114176319631361|date=15 June 2016|title=Tom Elliott has become the 2nd former leader of the UUP (Trimble is the other) to say he'll be voting Leave next week.|accessdate=23 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n====Independent====\n* [[David Owen|Lord Owen]], currently an independent Social Democrat peer, former [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] [[Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs|Foreign Secretary]] and leader (and co-founder) of the [[Social Democratic Party (UK)|Social Democratic Party]].<ref name=\"OwenGuardian\">{{cite news|title=Leaving the EU could 're-energise' Britain, says David Owen|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/feb/24/eu-beyond-reform-says-former-foreign-secretary-lord-owen|accessdate=26 February 2016|work=The Guardian|agency=Press Association|date=24 February 2016}}</ref>\n* [[John Taylor, Baron Kilclooney|Lord Kilclooney]], currently a [[crossbench]] peer, former [[Ulster Unionist Party]] MP and MEP.<ref name=\"TaylorNewsLetter\">{{cite news|title=I am strongly pro Europe and I was an MEP but now I back Brexit|url=http://www.newsletter.co.uk/news/i-am-strongly-pro-europe-and-i-was-an-mep-but-now-i-back-brexit-1-7243302|accessdate=2 March 2016|work=The Newsletter|date=2 March 2016}}</ref>\n* [[David Stoddart, Baron Stoddart of Swindon|Lord Stoddart]], member of the [[House of Lords]] since 1983 (formerly a Labour peer) and Independent Labour peer since 2002.<ref>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9SmmNKeoShc|title=Cameron hawking around EU disgraceful|work=[[RT UK]]|date=3 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cb0qtyLaXGA|title='EU ref is conspiracy of Bankers vs Brits' \u2013 Lord Stoddart|work=[[RT UK]]|date=9 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n===International figures===\n\n==== From other European Union member states ====\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n*[[Thomas Pringle (politician)|Thomas Pringle]], member of the [[D\u00e1il \u00c9ireann]] of Ireland<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oceanfm.ie/pringle-the-sky-wont-fall-in-if-a-brexit-comes-to-pass/|title=Pringle: 'The sky won't fall in' if a Brexit comes to pass \u2013 Ocean FM|date=22 April 2016|accessdate=23 June 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160423123711/http://oceanfm.ie/pringle-the-sky-wont-fall-in-if-a-brexit-comes-to-pass/|archivedate=23 April 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Jimmie \u00c5kesson]], chairman of the [[Sweden Democrats]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Sweden's nationalist party backs EU Brexit|url=http://www.thelocal.se/20160308/swedens-anti-immigration-party-backs-eu-brexit|website=The Local|accessdate=8 March 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Michel Debray]], French admiral and politician<ref name=\"express.co.uk\">{{cite web|url=http://www.express.co.uk/news/uk/679248/Brexit-stop-Brussels-creating-dangerous-EU-army-European-Union-French-admirals-say|title=Brexit will STOP Brussels creating a 'DANGEROUS' EU army, senior French admirals say|first=Charlie|last=Peat|date=13 June 2016|accessdate=23 June 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Janusz Korwin-Mikke]] MEP, leader of the Polish [[Coalition for the Renewal of the Republic\u2013Liberty and Hope]]<ref>{{cite news|work=[[Sputnik (news agency)|Sputnik]]|url=http://sputniknews.com/europe/20160531/1040546109/poland-eu-occupation.html|title='Poland is Dying Under EU Occupation': Warsaw Should Follow British Suit|date=31 May 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Marine Le Pen]] MEP, leader of the French [[National Front (France)|National Front]] and co-chair of the [[Europe of Nations and Freedom]]<ref name=\"UKinEU\">{{cite web|title=UK in the EU: MEPs debate the country's European future|date=24 February 2016|accessdate=26 February 2016|work=European Parliament News|url=http://www.europarl.europa.eu/news/en/news-room/20160224STO15605/UK-in-the-EU-MEPs-debate-the-country%E2%80%99s-European-future}}</ref>\n*[[Marion Mar\u00e9chal-Le Pen]], French MP and member of the National Front<ref name=\"Twitter\">{{cite tweet|user=Marion_M_Le_Pen|author=Marion Le Pen|number=701128746066120704|date=20 February 2016|title=Le 23 juin prochain, la GB aura l'occasion de devenir un mod\u00e8le pour toutes les nations europ\u00e9ennes en qu\u00eate de souverainet\u00e9. #Brexit}}</ref>\n*Professor [[Anthony Coughlan]], secretary of [[The National Platform for EU Research and Information Centre]] and retired Senior Lecturer Emeritus in Social Policy at [[Trinity College, Dublin]]<ref name=\"youtube.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AhrUSdNxHic|title=IRISH FOR BREXIT 1|last=MrJamesD29|date=1 June 2016|accessdate=23 June 2016|via=YouTube}}{{better source|date=June 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Luke 'Ming' Flanagan]], Irish [[Independent politician|independent]] MEP and former [[Teachta D\u00e1la|TD]]<ref name=\"youtube.com\"/>\n*[[Karmenu Mifsud Bonnici]], former [[Prime Minister of Malta]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20160307/local/how-maltese-can-have-a-say-in-uk-brexit-referendum.604701|title=How Maltese can have a say in UK 'Brexit' referendum|author=Allied Newspapers Ltd|work=The Times|location=Malta}}</ref>\n*[[Florian Philippot]], vice-president of the French [[Front National]]<ref name=\"libelbrexitreveille\">{{cite news|last1=Moreau|first1=Sylvain|title=Le Brexit r\u00e9veille les eurosceptiques fran\u00e7ais|url=http://www.liberation.fr/france/2016/02/22/le-brexit-reveille-les-eurosceptiques-francais_1435020|accessdate=3 March 2016|work=Lib\u00e9ration|date=22 February 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Patricia McKenna]], Irish [[Independent politician|independent]] Green politician and former MEP<ref>{{cite web|url=http://green-leaves.org/team/|title=Our Team|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160520135038/http://green-leaves.org/team/|archivedate=20 May 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Matteo Salvini]] MEP, leader of the Italian [[Lega Nord|Northern League]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.iltempo.it/adn-kronos/2016/06/13/ue-salvini-brexit-possibile-fine-incubo-da-tusk-terrorismo-mediatico-1.1549309|title=EU: Salvini, Brexit nightmare can end, as Tusk media terrorism|date=13 June 2016|work=[[Il Tempo]]|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614113321/http://www.iltempo.it/adn-kronos/2016/06/13/ue-salvini-brexit-possibile-fine-incubo-da-tusk-terrorismo-mediatico-1.1549309|archivedate=14 June 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Jonas Sj\u00f6stedt]], chairman of the [[V\u00e4nsterpartiet|Swedish Left Party]]<ref name=\"Brexeunt\">{{cite web|title=Brexeunt stage left: the Europeans hoping that Britain votes Brexit|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/may/18/brexeunt-stage-left-europeans-hoping-b