eo McKinstry: Germany controls the EU, we MUST get out NOW|first=Leo|last=McKinstry|date=30 June 2014|accessdate=23 June 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Noel Malcolm]], journalist, historian and academic<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.spectator.co.uk/2016/05/the-great-eu-power-trap/|title=The great EU power trap|date=28 May 2016|accessdate=23 June 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Carole Malone]], journalist and broadcaster<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/uk-news/david-cameron-bends-rules-over-8167010|title=David Cameron bends the rules over EU referendum to suit his own agenda|first=Carole|last=Malone|date=11 June 2016|accessdate=23 June 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Tim Montgomerie]], blogger, columnist of [[The Times]] and creator of [[ConservativeHome]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/opinion/columnists/article4459680.ece|title=Why Britain is better off leaving Europe|work=The Times|last1=Montgomerie|first1=Tim}}</ref>\n*[[Charles Moore (journalist)|Charles Moore]], journalist and former editor of ''The Daily Telegraph''<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/eureferendum/12183729/Our-pompous-bigoted-elite-have-not-even-bothered-to-consider-the-case-for-Brexit.html|title=Our pompous, bigoted elite have not even bothered to consider the case for Brexit|date=4 March 2016|accessdate=23 June 2016|last1=Moore|first1=Charles}}</ref>\n*[[Jane Moore]], journalist and TV presenter{{cn|date=March 2020}}\n*[[Douglas Murray (author)|Douglas Murray]], journalist and writer<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nationalreview.com/magazine/2016-06-13-0100/brexit-european-union-lose-united-kingdom|title=Exit Britain?|date=13 June 2016|accessdate=23 June 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Fraser Nelson]], editor of ''[[The Spectator]]''<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.24liveblog.com/share/194405300?url=http://blogs.spectator.co.uk/2016/06/live-eu-referendum-wembley-debate/|title=Archived copy|access-date=8 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161006125330/http://www.24liv