iqTpQReY8|title=#Brexit: #ProjectFear is Ridiculous|last=Sargon of Akkad|date=18 May 2016|via=YouTube}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=JW0LEtW_6sI|title=The Financial Argument for #Brexit (#VoteLeave #VoteRemain #StrongerIn)|last=Sargon of Akkad|date=15 June 2016|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n*[[Dia Chakravarty]], activist<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/iplayer/episode/b077nv3b/question-time-14042016|title=BBC iPlayer \u2013 Question Time \u2013 14/04/2016|work=BBC iPlayer}}</ref>\n*[[Roy Chubby Brown]], comedian<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dailypost.co.uk/whats-on/roy-chubby-brown-brexit-immigrants-13683187|title=Roy Chubby Brown on Brexit, Jeremy Corbyn and being called racist|first=Zara|last=Whelan|date=27 September 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Piers Corbyn]], owner of WeatherAction and brother of [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] leader [[Jeremy Corbyn]]<ref>{{cite tweet|number=708436036486090754|user=Piers_Corbyn|title=WELL DONE #BernieSanders! WE MUST...|accessdate= 27 March 2016 |date= 11 March 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Gillian Duffy]], a woman who [[Gordon Brown]] referred to as a 'bigot' in the [[Entrepreneurs' letter|2010 election campaign]] (\"bigotgate\").<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/video_and_audio/features/uk-politics-eu-referendum-36373649/36373649 Gillian Duffy: 'I don't want to be a European'], BBC, 25 May 2016 (Video)</ref>\n*[[Martin Durkin (television director)|Martin Durkin]], television director<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.iea.org.uk/multimedia/video/martin-durkin-why-the-uk-must-leave-the-eu |title=Martin Durkin: Why the UK Must Leave the EU &#124; Institute of Economic Affairs |website=Iea.org.uk |accessdate=12 May 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Matthew Elliott (politics)|Matthew Elliott]], founder of the [[TaxPayers' Alliance]] and [[Big Brother Watch]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.businessinsider.com/matthew-elliott-and-dominic-cummings-exit-vote-leave-board-2016-2|title=Matthew Elliott and Dominic Cummings exit Vote Leave board \u2013 Business I