pean Union membership referendum]]\n[[Category:Political endorsements in the United Kingdom|European Union membership referendum, 2016]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2020}}\n{{Brexit sidebar}}\n{{Expand list|date=April 2016}}\nA number of politicians, public figures, newspapers and magazines, businesses and other organisations endorsed either the United Kingdom remaining in the EU or the United Kingdom leaving the EU during the [[2016 United Kingdom European Union membership referendum]].\n\n==Remain==\n\n===Government===\n\n====Territories voting in referendum====\n* [[Government of the United Kingdom]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eureferendum.gov.uk/|title=EU Referendum \u2013 Information from the UK Government|publisher=[[Government of the United Kingdom]]|date=26 May 2016|accessdate=19 June 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Scottish Government]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-36383590|title=EU referendum debate: MSPs vote overwhelmingly for UK to remain in EU|date=26 May 2016 |accessdate=27 May 2016|work=BBC News}}</ref>\n* [[Welsh Government]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gov.wales/newsroom/firstminister/2016/160518fmwales/?lang=en|title=Statement by the First Minister of Wales: Moving Wales Forward|date=18 May 2016|accessdate=27 May 2016|author=Carwyn Jones|author-link=Carwyn Jones}}</ref>\n* [[Government of Gibraltar]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.euroweeklynews.com/3.0.15/news/on-euro-weekly-news/gibraltar-news/137143-gibraltar-government-to-support-%E2%80%98stay%E2%80%99-vote-in-eu-referendum |title=Gibraltar Government to support 'STAY' vote in EU Referendum |website=Euroweeklynews.com |accessdate=3 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n====Other Crown dependencies====\n* [[Government of Jersey]]\n* [[Government of Guernsey]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.itv.com/news/channel/2016-05-23/jersey-and-guernsey-governments-support-uk-remaining/|title=Jersey and Guernsey governments support UK remaining i