ay in EU |work=The Daily Telegraph|date= 21 May 2015|accessdate=27 May 2015|last1=Johnson |first1=Simon }}</ref>\n* [[Scottish Green Party]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scottishgreens.org.uk/uncategorized/eu-referendum-greens-to-make-progressive-case-for-membership/|title=\u00bb EU Referendum: Greens to Make Progressive Case for Membership|date=10 October 2015|publisher=Scottish Greens|accessdate=8 December 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117024353/https://www.scottishgreens.org.uk/uncategorized/eu-referendum-greens-to-make-progressive-case-for-membership/|archivedate=17 November 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Scottish Socialist Party]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scottishsocialistparty.org/the-socialist-case-against-leaving-the-european-union/|title=The Socialist Case Against Leaving the European Union|work=Scottish Socialist Party|date=15 February 2016}}</ref>\n\n'''Parties in Northern Ireland:'''\n* [[Alliance Party of Northern Ireland]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://allianceparty.org/article/2015/0009715/dickson-an-eu-referendum-will-threaten-jobs-and-investment-in-northern-ireland|title=Dickson \u2013 An EU referendum will threaten jobs and investment in Northern Ireland|date=14 May 2015|publisher=The Alliance Party of Northern Ireland|accessdate=8 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117024840/http://allianceparty.org/article/2015/0009715/dickson-an-eu-referendum-will-threaten-jobs-and-investment-in-northern-ireland|archive-date=17 November 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://allianceparty.org/article/2015/0009695/alliance-expresses-concerns-over-referendum-idea|title=Alliance expresses concerns over referendum idea|date=29 April 2015|publisher=The Alliance Party of Northern Ireland|accessdate=8 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117030051/http://allianceparty.org/article/2015/0009695/alliance-expresses-concerns-over-referendum-idea|archive-date=17 November 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* [[Green Party in Northern Ireland]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.greenpartyni.org/www/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Westminster2015.pdf|title=Green Party in Northern Ireland: Manifesto 2015|publisher=Green Party in Northern Ireland|accessdate=22 December 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151118003739/http://www.greenpartyni.org/www/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Westminster2015.pdf|archivedate=18 November 2015}}</ref>\n* [[NI21]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/opinion/debateni/john-mccallister/anna-lo-has-right-to-aspire-to-united-ireland-but-the-alliance-member-has-dragged-us-back-into-tribal-politics-30127267.html|title=Anna Lo has right to aspire to united Ireland but the Alliance member has dragged us back into tribal politics|author=John McCallister|date=26 March 2014|newspaper=The Belfast Telegraph|accessdate=8 December 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Sinn F\u00e9in]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/news/northern-ireland/sinn-fein-to-protect-eu-membership-31156231.html|title=Sinn Fein to protect EU membership|date=20 April 2015|work=The Belfast Telegraph|accessdate=8 December 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Social Democratic and Labour Party]] (SDLP)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sdlp.ie/issues/international-affairs/|title=International Affairs|work=Social Democratic and Labour Party|accessdate=8 December 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151203135002/http://www.sdlp.ie/issues/international-affairs/|archivedate=3 December 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Ulster Unionist Party]] (UUP)<ref>{{cite web|last=UUP|author-link=Ulster Unionist Party|url=http://uup.org/news/4155/21/Statement-from-the-Ulster-Unionist-Party#.VtrhT0DJaob/|title=Statement from the Ulster Unionist Party on EU Referendum|publisher=[[Ulster Unionist Party]]|accessdate=5 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n'''Parties in Wales:'''\n* [[Plaid Cymru]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.partyof.wales/europe-1/|title=Europe|work=Plaid Cymru|url-status