ler' for London \u2013 Bloomberg Business |publisher=Bloomberg L.P. |date=9 November 2015 |accessdate=2 March 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Nicolas Sarkozy]], former President of France<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/05/17/brexit-debate-is-opportunity-to-re-found-europe-says-sarkozy/ |title=Brexit debate is 'opportunity to re-found Europe', says Sarkozy |newspaper=The Telegraph |accessdate=17 May 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Wolfgang Sch\u00e4uble]], Minister of Finance of Germany<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-britain-eu-germany-idUKKCN0W51QS|title=EU would be less stable without UK \u2013 Germany's Schaeuble|date=3 March 2016|agency=Reuters UK}}</ref>\n*[[Jaap De Hoop Scheffer]], former [[Secretary-General of NATO]] (2004\u201309)<ref name=\"NATOLetter\">{{cite news|title=Letters: At a time of global instability, Britain needs to stand united with its EU allie|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/opinion/2016/05/09/letters-at-a-time-of-global-instability-britain-needs-to-stand-u/|newspaper=The Telegraph|date=10 May 2016|accessdate=10 May 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Rados\u0142aw Sikorski]], former Minister of Foreign Affairs of [[Poland]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://bigstory.ap.org/article/b212dd2d2dfd457ab0adc28e906326e8/ap-interview-polish-ex-foreign-minister-sees-brexit-dangers|title=AP Interview: Polish ex-foreign minister sees Brexit dangers  |agency=Associated Press|accessdate=17 May 2016 }}</ref>\n*[[Juha Sipil\u00e4]], Prime Minister of Finland<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.finlandtimes.fi/national/2016/02/18/25222/Sipil%C3%A4-hopes-Britain-will-stay-in-EU |title= Sipil\u00e4 hopes Britain will stay in EU |work=Finland Times|accessdate=6 March 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Bohuslav Sobotka]], Prime Minister of Czech Republic<ref>{{cite web|url=http://praguemonitor.com/2016/02/22/sobotka-deal-good-compromise-can-help-keep-uk-eu |title= Sobotka: Deal is good compromise, can help keep UK in EU |publisher=Prague Daily Monitor|accessdate=6 March 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Javie