ssdate = 10 March 2016 | newspaper = [[The Daily Telegraph]] | date = 10 March 2016}}</ref> more than 150 notable academics, all [[Fellow of the Royal Society|Fellows]] of the [[Royal Society]], signed a letter to ''[[The Times]]'' newspaper setting out their position on the European Union that leaving the bloc would damage science and research. They included:<ref name=Times2016-03-09>{{cite news | title =Letters to the Editor \u2013 More than 150 eminent Cambridge academics explain why leaving the EU would be a disaster for UK science  | newspaper = [[The Times]] | date = 9 March 2016| url =  http://www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/opinion/letters/article4709281.ece | access-date = 11 March 2016 }} Mirrored at {{cite web|url=http://www.strongerin.co.uk/more_than_150_eminent_cambridge_academics_explain_why_leaving_the_eu_would_be_a_disaster_for_uk_science | title = More than 150 top scientists explain why leaving the EU would be a disaster | website = Britain Stronger in Europe | accessdate = 11 March 2016}}</ref>\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n*[[Michael Akam]], [[ForMemRS|FRS]], zoologist\n*[[Ali Alavi]], [[ForMemRS|FRS]], Professor of Theoretical Chemistry\n*[[Ross J. Anderson|Ross Anderson]], [[ForMemRS|FRS]], Professor of Security Engineering\n*[[Shankar Balasubramanian]], [[ForMemRS|FRS]], Professor of Medicinal Chemistry\n*[[Andrew Balmford]], [[ForMemRS|FRS]], Professor of Conservation Science\n*[[David Barford]], [[ForMemRS|FRS]], Professor of Molecular Biology\n*[[John D. Barrow]], [[ForMemRS|FRS]], Professor of Mathematical Sciences\n*[[Mike Bate|Michael Bate]], [[ForMemRS|FRS]], zoologist\n*Sir [[David Baulcombe]], scientist\n*Sir [[Harshad Bhadeshia|Harshad Badeshia]], [[ForMemRS|FRS]], Professor of Metallurgy\n*[[Michael Bickle]], [[ForMemRS|FRS]], Professor of Geophysics, Geodynamics and Tectonics\n*[[Mariann Bienz]], [[ForMemRS|FRS]], molecular biologist\n*Sir [[Tom Blundell]], scientist and president of the [[Science Council]]\n*[[Martin Bobrow]], [[ForMemRS