]] CBE, director and producer\n*[[Stephen Frears]], director\n*[[Stephen Woolley]], producer, director\n*[[Steve Coogan]], actor, producer, writer\n*[[Steve McQueen (director)|Steve McQueen]], director\n*[[Tacita Dean]], artist\n*[[Thandie Newton]], actress\n*[[Thea Sharrock]], director\n*[[Thomas Heatherwick]], designer\n*[[Tim Bevan]], co-chairman, Working Title Films\n*[[Tim Pigott-Smith]], actor, director, writer\n*[[Tom Geens]], director\n*[[Tom Harper (director)|Tom Harper]], director\n*[[Tom Hooper]], director\n*[[Tony Bevan]], artist\n*[[Tracey Emin]], artist\n*[[Tracey Seaward]], producer\n*[[Vicky Featherstone]], Artistic Director of the Royal Court Theatre, London\n*[[Wayne McGregor]] CBE, Choreographer and founder of Studio Wayne McGregor\n*[[Wolfgang Tillmans]] RA Artist\n*[[Yana Peel]], CEO of the Serpentine Galleries\n}}\n\n==== Economists' letter ====\nIn a letter to ''The Times'', 279 economists stated that Brexit would \"entail significant long-term costs\". The signatories wrote, \"focusing entirely on the economics, we consider that it would be a major mistake for the UK to leave the European Union.\" At the time of publication the letter had 199 signatories. A further 80 signed after publication.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/economists-warn-against-brexit-vote-bh07fdx0t|title=Economists warn against Brexit vote|website=The Times|access-date=24 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cep.lse.ac.uk/textonly/_new2014/BREXIT/BREXIT_LETTER_23May2016.pdf|title=The letter: [published in The Times, 11.05.16]|website=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://longandvariable.wordpress.com/2016/05/23/280-economists-now-against-brexit-as-ucl-and-lse-sign/|title=280 economists now against Brexit as UCL and LSE sign|first=Tony|last=Yates|date=23 May 2016}}</ref>\n\n==== Lawyers' report ====\nAround 300 lawyers signed a report on UK membership of the EU and the alternatives. They stated: \"we recognised how much of the debate on the UK's membership of the EU is based on a lack of information, misconceptions, or, worse, misinformation [...] Ultimately, we believe a sensible judgment on EU membership can be made only on the basis of reliable evidence\". The signatories \"consider that the UK's interests are best served by remaining in the EU\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lawyers-inforbritain.uk/signatories/|title=Signatories|date=29 February 2016}}</ref>\n\n==== Historians letter ====\nIn a letter to the Guardian, more than 300 prominent historians urged the United Kingdom to remain in the European Union. The letter said, \"On 23 June, we face a choice: to cast ourselves adrift, condemning ourselves to irrelevance and Europe to division and weakness; or to reaffirm our commitment to the EU and stiffen the cohesion of our continent in a dangerous world.\" Notable signatories included:<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/may/24/lessons-from-history-for-the-brexiteers|title=Lessons from history for the Brexiteers {{!}} Letters from Simon Schama and others and Jack Dromey MP|last=Letters|date=24 May 2016|website=The Guardian|access-date=25 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/may/25/vote-to-leave-eu-will-condemn-britain-to-irrelevance-say-historians|title=Vote to leave EU would 'condemn Britain to irrelevance', say historians|last=Stewart|first=Heather|date=25 May 2016|website=The Guardian|access-date=25 May 2016}}</ref>\n{{columns-list|colwidth=18em|\n*Professor [[Simon Schama]]\n*Professor [[Ian Kershaw]]\n*Professor [[Niall Ferguson]]\n*Dr [[Juliet Gardiner]]\n*[[D. R. Thorpe]]\n*Professor [[David Runciman]]\n*[[Richard Davenport-Hines]]\n*Professor [[Colin Jones (historian)|Colin Jones]]\n*Professor [[Michael Burleigh]]\n*Professor [[R. F. Foster (historian)|Roy Foster]]\n*Dr [[Marc Morris]]\n*Dr [[Suzannah Lipscomb]]\n*Professor [[Ali Ansari]]\n*[[Robert Lacey]]\n*Professor [[Richard Overy]]\n*Professor [[Beatrice Heuser]]\n*Professor [[Richard Bessel]]\n*Professor [[Patricia Clavin]]\n*Professor [[Dominic Lieven]]\n*Professor [[Keith Thomas (historian)|Keith Thomas]]\n}}\n\n====Armed Forces and Security Services====\n* [[Jonathan Evans, Baron Evans of Weardale|Sir Jonathan Evans]], former [[Director General of MI5]]<ref name=\"The Sunday Times\">{{cite news|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/edition/news/spy-chiefs-say-quitting-eu-is-security-risk-fgzgpgkgk|title=Spy chiefs say quitting EU is security risk|newspaper=The Sunday Times|date=8 May 2016|accessdate=8 May 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Eliza Manningham-Buller]], former [[Director General of MI5]]<ref name=\"The Guardian\">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/may/11/britain-less-safe-outside-eu-former-mi5-chief-eliza-manningham-buller|title='Britain less safe outside EU', says former M15 Chief Eliza Manningham Buller|newspaper=The Guardian|date=11 May 2016|accessdate=11 May 2016}}</ref>\n* [[John Sawers|Sir John Sawers]], former [[Chief of the Secret Intelligence Service]]([[Secret Intelligence Service|MI6]])<ref name=\"The Sunday Times\"/>\n* Sir [[Hugh Orde]], former president of the [[Association of Chief Police Officers]], and former Chief Constable of the [[Police Service of Northern Ireland]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=Watt|first1=Nicholas|title=EU exit would make UK a magnet for fugitives, warns former Acpo chief|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/oct/12/eu-referendum-uk-exit-safe-haven-fugitives-hugh-orde-acpo|accessdate=23 March 2016|work=The Guardian}}</ref>\n* [[Lynne Owens]], [[Director-General of the National Crime Agency]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.sky.com/story/1677285/warning-over-crime-risk-if-uk-leaves-eu|title=Warning Over Crime Risk If UK Leaves EU|publisher=Sky News}}</ref>\n* [[Richard Dannatt|General Lord Dannatt]], former [[Chief of the General Staff]]<ref name=\"autogenerated2\">{{cite news|title=UK safer inside EU, former defence chiefs say|work=BBC News|date=24 February 2016|url=https