obel Prize laureates letter====\nOn 10 June 2016, ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'' published a letter signed by 13 winners of the Nobel Prize expressing the view that being part of the EU is good for British science and that is good for Britain.<ref>{{cite news | title = Letters | newspaper = [[The Daily Telegraph]] | date = 10 June 2016 | url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/opinion/2016/06/10/letters-eu-campaigners-have-lost-support-by-shouting-and-persona/ | access-date = 11 June 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Sydney Brenner|Dr Sydney Brenner]], Laureate, Physiology or Medicine 2002\n* [[Martin Evans|Sir Martin Evans]], Laureate, Physiology or Medicine 2007\n* [[Andre Geim|Sir Andre Geim]], Laureate, Physics 2010\n* [[John Gurdon|Sir John Gurdon]], Laureate, Physiology or Medicine 2012\n* [[Peter Higgs|Professor Peter Higgs]], Laureate, Physics 2013\n* [[Tim Hunt|Sir Tim Hunt]], Laureate, Physiology or Medicine 2001\n* [[Tomas Lindahl|Dr Tomas Lindahl]], Laureate, Chemistry 2015\n* [[Konstantin Novoselov|Sir Kostya Novoselov]], Laureate, Physics 2010\n* [[Paul Nurse|Sir Paul Nurse]], Laureate, Physiology or Medicine 2001\n* [[John O'Keefe (neuroscientist)|Professor John O'Keefe]], Laureate, Physiology or Medicine 2014\n* [[Richard J. Roberts|Sir Richard Roberts]], Laureate, Physiology or Medicine 1993\n* [[John Sulston|Sir John Sulston]], Laureate, Physiology or Medicine 2002\n* [[John E. Walker|Sir John Walker]], Laureate, Chemistry 1997\n\n====Nobel Prize in Economics laureates letter====\nOn 19 June 2016, ''[[The Guardian]]'' published a letter signed by 10 winners of the [[Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences]], expressing the view that the \"economic argument\" was clearly in favour of continued UK membership within the EU.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/jun/19/we-nobel-prize-winning-economists-believe-the-uk-is-better-off-in-the-eu|title=We Nobel prize-winning economists believe the UK is better off in the EU \u2013 Letters|last=Letters|date=19 June 2016|accessdate=23 June 2016}}</ref>\n* [[George Akerlof]], Laureate, 2001\n* [[Kenneth Arrow]], Laureate, 1972\n* [[Angus Deaton]], Laureate, 2015\n* [[Peter Diamond]], Laureate, 2010\n* [[James Heckman]], Laureate, 2000\n* [[Eric Maskin]], Laureate, 2007\n* Sir [[James Mirrlees]], Laureate, 1996\n* [[Christopher A. Pissarides]], Laureate, 2010\n* [[Robert Solow]], Laureate, 1987\n* [[Jean Tirole]], Laureate, 2014\n\n==Leave==\n\n===Registered political parties===\n'''Parties organised in more than one of the Home Nations:'''\n* [[British Democratic Party (2013)|British Democratic Party]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://search.electoralcommission.org.uk/English/Registrations/PP1765|title=View registration \u2013 The Electoral Commission}}</ref>\n* [[Britain First]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.britainfirst.org/minister-blasts-relentless-campaign-of-fear-over-brexit/ |title=MINISTER BLASTS \"RELENTLESS CAMPAIGN OF FEAR' OVER BREXIT\" |website=Britainfirst.org |accessdate=3 March 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306034101/http://www.britainfirst.org/minister-blasts-relentless-campaign-of-fear-over-brexit/ |archive-date=6 March 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.britainfirst.org/eu-plots-military-merger-if-uk-votes-to-stay-in/ |title=EU PLOTS MILITARY MERGER IF UK VOTES TO STAY IN |website=Britainfirst.org |accessdate=3 March 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306033448/http://www.britainfirst.org/eu-plots-military-merger-if-uk-votes-to-stay-in/ |archive-date=6 March 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[British National Party]] (BNP)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bnp.org.uk/policies/foreign-affairs|title=British National Party}}</ref>\n* [[Liberal Party (UK, 1989)|Liberal Party]]<ref name=\"leaflet\"/>\n* [[Independence from Europe]]<ref>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JO2ij6EorAc|title=AN INDEPENDENCE FROM EUROPE YOUTUBE|date=19 April 2014|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n* [[Liberty GB]]<ref>{{cite w