/workersparty.ie/lexit-the-socialist-case-for-voting-leave/|title=LEXIT: the socialist case for voting 'Leave'|work=The Workers' Party of Ireland|access-date=27 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Business leaders===\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n*[[Baron Bamford|Anthony Bamford]], businessman and chairman of JCB<ref>{{cite tweet|user=Opera_Singer_|author=Michael|number=740521624143794176|date=8 June 2016|title=JCB Chairman Lord Bamford has sent all his employees this letter about the #EUref! #VoteLeave #Brexit|accessdate=23 June 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Arron Banks]], businessman<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/eureferendum/11688911/Millionaires-prepare-to-launch-20million-non-political-campaign-for-Britain-to-quit-European-Union.html|title=Millionaires prepare to launch \u00a320million non-political campaign for Britain to quit European Union|date=21 June 2015|work=The Daily Telegraph|last1=Hope|first1=Christopher}}</ref>\n*[[Duncan Bannatyne]], entrepreneur, philanthropist and author.<ref>{{cite tweet|number=529226735326593024|user=DuncanBannatyne|title=We must leave the EU,..... MUST|accessdate= 26 March 2016 |date= 3 November 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Robin Birley (businessman)|Robin Birley]], businessman<ref name=\"voteleavetakecontrol.org\">{{cite web|url=http://www.voteleavetakecontrol.org/250_business_leaders_back_vote_leave_as_new_poll_shows_eu_stops_entrepreneurs_creating_jobs|title=250 business leaders back Vote Leave, as new poll shows EU stops entrepreneurs creating jobs|work=Vote Leave|accessdate=26 March 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160329040758/http://www.voteleavetakecontrol.org/250_business_leaders_back_vote_leave_as_new_poll_shows_eu_stops_entrepreneurs_creating_jobs|archivedate=29 March 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Harriet Bridgeman]], founder of the [[Bridgeman Art Library]]<ref name=\"voteleavetakecontrol.org\"/>\n*[[Dominic Burke (businessman)|Dominic Burke]], CEO of [[Jardine Lloyd Thompson]]<ref name=\"telegraph.co