-breaks-ranks-to-make-left-wing-case-for-brexit/|title=Labour MSP breaks ranks to make 'left-wing' case for Brexit|author=Aiden Kerr|publisher=STV|date=26 May 2016|accessdate=27 May 2016}}</ref>\n\nFormer Labour MPs:\n* [[Tom Harris (British politician)|Tom Harris]] ([[Glasgow South (UK Parliament constituency)|Glasgow South]] (2001\u20132015)<ref name=\"autogenerated4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-35841224|title=EU referendum: Tom Harris to head Scottish Vote Leave campaign|work=BBC News|accessdate=19 March 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Ian Davidson (British politician)|Ian Davidson]] ([[Glasgow South West (UK Parliament constituency)|Glasgow South West]] (1992\u20132015)<ref name=\"autogenerated4\"/>\n* [[Austin Mitchell]] ([[Great Grimsby (UK Parliament constituency)|Great Grimsby]] (1977\u20132015)<ref name=\"labourleave1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.labourleave.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/The-Labour-Case-for-Brexit.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=10 June 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614212515/http://www.labourleave.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/The-Labour-Case-for-Brexit.pdf |archivedate=14 June 2016 }}</ref>\n* [[Nigel Griffiths]] ([[Edinburgh South (UK Parliament constituency)|Edinburgh South]] 1987\u20132010)<ref name=\"autogenerated4\"/>\n\n====Green Party====\nWithin the [[Green Party of England and Wales|Green Party]] (which supported Remain): the Green Leaves organisation campaigned on behalf of Green Party members who advocated a leave vote.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://green-leaves.org/|title=Home}}</ref> Member of the House of Lords and former London Assembly Member [[Jenny Jones, Baroness Jones of Moulsecoomb|Jenny Jones]] (Baroness Jones) campaigned to leave.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2015/10/09/european-referendum-vote-leave-campaign-launched-political-donors_n_8267464.html|title=European Referendum: Vote Leave Campaign Launched, Bankrolled By Three of Britain's Biggest Political Donors|work=The Huffington Post UK}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theecologist.org/blogs_and_comments/commentators/2946192/something_rotten_in_the_state_of_europe.html|title=Something rotten in the state of Europe|date=13 July 2015|work=The Ecologist}}</ref>\n\n====Liberal Democrats====\nWithin the [[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrats]] (which supported Remain): the Liberal Leave campaign<ref>{{cite web|url=http://liberalleave.org/|title=Liberal Leave \u2013 Liberal Leave}}</ref> was headed by former [[Hereford (UK Parliament constituency)|Hereford]] MP, [[Paul Keetch]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/voices/think-that-if-you-are-liberal-you-should-vote-to-stay-in-the-eu-think-again-a6916921.html|title=Think that if you are liberal you should vote to stay in the EU? Think again|author=Paul Keetch|date=7 March 2016|work=The Independent}}</ref>\n\n====Scottish National Party====\nWithin the [[Scottish National Party|SNP]] (which supports Remain): former SNP deputy leader and MP [[Jim Sillars]] and former SNP leader and MP [[Gordon Wilson (Scottish politician)|Gordon Wilson]] endorsed a leave vote in the referendum.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/scottish-news/snp-stalwart-jim-sillars-campaign-7219127|title=SNP stalwart Jim Sillars will campaign to leave Europe and says lots of nationalists agree with him|author=Record|date=21 January 2016|work=dailyrecord}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thenational.scot/politics/jim-sillars-capital-calls-the-tune-in-eu-thats-why-we-should-go.16502|title=Jim Sillars: Capital calls the tune in EU \u2013 that's why we should go|work=thenational.scot}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.heraldscotland.com/news/14316092.Jim_Sillars__Nationalists_must_vote_to_leave_EU_if_Scotland_is_to_become_truly_sovereign/|title=Jim Sillars: Nationalists must vote to leave EU if Scotland is to become truly sovereign|work=The Herald|location=Glasgow}}</ref> Former Scottish government minister [[Alex Neil (politician)|Alex Neil]] declared that he has voted leave and that several of his fellow SNP MSPs did likewise.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.heraldscotland.com/news/14843960.Alex_Neil__I_voted_for_Brexit_and_I_was_not_the_only_SNP_MSP_who_backed_leave/|title=Alex Neil: I voted for Brexit and I was not the only SNP MSP who backed leave|website=The Herald|location=Glasgow}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-37870167|title=SNP ex-minister Alex Neil voted for Brexit|date=4 November 2016|via=bbc.com}}</ref> There are multiple groups for SNP members advocating a leave vote, such as ''SNP Vote Leave'' and ''SNP GO!''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.express.co.uk/news/uk/675954/Scotland-SNP-Nicola-Sturgeon-EU-vote-Remain-out-UK-Dundee|title=New blow for Sturgeon's fight to stay in EU as SNP activists launch new Out drive|date=31 May 2016|accessdate=23 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n====Ulster Unionist Party====\nWithin the [[Ulster Unionist Party|UUP]] (which supports Remain): [[Harold McKee]] MLA<ref>{{cite tweet|user=NIVote_Leave|author=NI Vote Leave|number=739128591053664256|date=4 June 2016|title=Thanks to Harold McKee MLA, @ccmccuup, @alexredpath1989, Cllr Dudgeon et al joining .@DanHannanMEP at final NI event|accessdate=23 June 2016}}</ref> and former leader [[Tom Elliott (politician)|Tom Elliot]] MP<ref>{{cite tweet|user=AlexKane221b|author=Alex.Kane|number=743114176319631361|date=15 June 2016|title=Tom Elliott has become the 2nd former leader of the UUP (Trimble is the other) to say he'll be voting Leave next week.|accessdate=23 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n====Independent====\n* [[David Owen|Lord Owen]], currently an independent Social Democrat peer, former [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] [[Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs|Foreign Secretary]] and leader (and co-founder) of the [[Social Democratic Party (UK)|Social Democratic Party]].<ref name=\"OwenGuardian\">{{cite news|title