y/18/brexeunt-stage-left-europeans-hoping-britain-votes-brexit?CMP=share_btn_link|website=The Guardian|accessdate=18 May 2016}}</ref> \n*[[Tom Van Grieken]], president of the Belgian [[Vlaams Belang]]<ref name=\"Brexeunt\" />\n*[[Geert Wilders]], leader of the Dutch [[Party for Freedom]]<ref>{{cite tweet|user=geertwilderspvv|author=Geert Wilders|number=727080550113132546|date=2 May 2016|title=I hope the proud British people vote for regaining national sovereignty instead of more Brussels on June 23. #Brexit}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==== Other countries ====\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n* [[John R. Bolton]], American diplomat and former US ambassador to the United Nations.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/eureferendum/12193719/Ignore-Obama-Brexit-will-make-the-Special-Relationship-even-more-special.html|title=Ignore Obama, Brexit will make the Special Relationship even more special|date=14 March 2016|work=The Daily Telegraph}}</ref>\n* [[Swapan Dasgupta]], senior Indian journalist and Member of Parliament in [[Rajya Sabha]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/right-and-wrong/forget-obamas-lecture-brexit-is-good-for-india/ |title=Forget Obama's lecture. Brexit is good for India. Swapan Dasgupta |work=The Times of India |accessdate=4 July 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Jim DeMint]], former [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] U.S. Senator from South Carolina and President of the [[Heritage Foundation]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dailysignal.com/2016/06/21/america-stands-with-the-uk-on-brexit/ |title=America Stands With UK on Brexit |publisher=Dailysignal.com |date=21 June 2016 |accessdate=4 July 2016}}</ref>\n* [[John Howard]], former [[Prime Minister of Australia]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.spectator.co.uk/2016/06/former-australian-pm-john-howard-backs-brexit/#|title=Former Australian PM John Howard backs Brexit \u2013 The Spectator|website=The Spectator}}</ref>\n* [[Gu\u00f0laugur \u00de\u00f3r \u00de\u00f3r\u00f0arso