abowo Subianto]], Chairman of [[Gerindra]] and Indonesian presidential candidate of both [[2014 Indonesian presidential election|2014]] and [[2019 Indonesian presidential election|2019]]\n}}\n\n===Businesses===\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n* [[Aspall Cider]], cider manufacturers<ref name=\"edp24.co.uk\">{{cite news|url=http://www.edp24.co.uk/business/east_anglia_business_leaders_launch_campaign_in_norwich_for_britain_to_leave_the_eu_1_4375641 |title=East Anglia business leaders launch campaign in Norwich for Britain to leave the EU |date=12 January 2016}}</ref>\n* [[JCB (company)|JCB]], manufacturing company<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/9c20e72a-fd57-11e4-9e96-00144feabdc0.html|title=JCB backing for EU exit sends tremors through business|newspaper=Financial Times}}</ref>\n* [[Tate and Lyle]], agribusiness<ref>{{cite news|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-britain-eu-tateandlylesugars-idUKKCN0WQ24R |title=Refiner Tate & Lyle Sugars says best served by Britain leaving EU |date=24 May 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Wetherspoons]], pub chain<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2016/may/31/wetherspoons-brexit-beer-mats-eu-referendum-imf|title=Pub chain JD Wetherspoon issues Brexit beer mats|first=Press|last=Association|date=31 May 2016|accessdate=23 June 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===Newspapers and magazines===\n<!-- Please include here only those media where a clear editorial position is given. Not columnists, not news reports. -->\n\n====British newspapers and magazines====\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n*''[[Daily Express]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.express.co.uk/web/europecrusade|archive-url=https://archive.is/20160113004951/http://www.express.co.uk/web/europecrusade|url-status=dead|archive-date=13 January 2016|title=Get Britain out of Europe|work=[[Daily Express]]}}</ref>\n*''[[Daily Mail]]''<ref name=reutersinst/>\n*''[[The Daily Telegraph]]''<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/opinion/2016/06/20/vote-leave-to-benefit-from-