rope, against the EU|work=[[Spiked (magazine)|Spiked]]}}</ref>\n*''[[The Jewish Chronicle]]''<ref>https://www.thejc.com/comment/comment/brexit-it-s-a-wonderful-day-for-britain-and-its-jews-1.59563?highlight=brexit</ref>\n*''[[The Sun (United Kingdom)|The Sun]]''<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/greenslade/2016/jun/14/the-suns-pro-brexit-campaigning-doesnt-cross-borders|title=The Sun's pro-Brexit campaign doesn't cross borders|newspaper=The Guardian}}</ref>\n*''[[The Sun on Sunday]]''<ref>https://www.pressgazette.co.uk/evening-standard-backs-remain-all-the-national-newspaper-brexit-vote-endorsements-at-a-glance/</ref>\n*''[[Sunday Express]]''<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.express.co.uk/comment/expresscomment/681115/Brexit-UK-referendum-vote-leave-EU|title=Today's Britain is strong, dynamic and influential. Let's keep it that way VOTE LEAVE|date=19 June 2016|accessdate=19 June 2016|newspaper=The Sunday Express}}</ref>\n*''[[Sunday Sport]]''<ref>{{cite tweet|user=thesundaysport|work=Sport|number=703672494125928449|date=27 February 2016|title=@Binxasaurus No, we're for Brexit \u2013 but that doesn't slant our coverage}}</ref>\n*''[[The Sunday Telegraph]]''<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/opinion/2016/06/18/we-must-vote-leave-to-create-a-britain-fit-for-the-future/|title=We must vote Leave to create a Britain fit for the future |work=[[The Sunday Telegraph]]|date=18 June 2016 }}</ref>\n*''[[The Sunday Times]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/time-for-britain-to-strike-a-new-deal-with-europe-vlszwk7jh?CMP=Spklr-_-Editorial-_-FBPAGE-_-TheTimesandTheSundayTimes-timesandsundaytimes-_-20160618-_-News-_-497164795-_-Image,textandlink&linkId=25687995|title=Time for Britain to strike a new deal with Europe|website=The Times|access-date=18 June 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n\n====Foreign newspapers and magazines====\n* ''[[National Review]]'', US current affairs magazine<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.nationalreview.com/article/436853/brexit-vote-restore-british-democracy-vote-leave|title=Why Britons should vote to Leave the EU|magazine=[[National Review]]}}</ref>\n\n===Local government authorities===\n* [[Bromley London Borough Council]] (Conservative controlled)<ref>{{cite web|title = Bromley council votes to leave European Union|url = http://www.bromleytimes.co.uk/news/bromley_council_votes_to_leave_european_union_1_4429842|website = Bromley Times|access-date = 23 February 2016|first = Tom|last = Pyman}}</ref>\n* [[Havering London Borough Council]] (Conservative-Residents controlled) became the first council in the UK to back Brexit.<ref>{{cite web|author=Pippa Crerar |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/politics/havering-council-becomes-first-in-britain-to-back-leaving-eu-a3167076.html |title=Havering council becomes first in Britain to back leaving EU |work=London Evening Standard |date=28 January 2016 |accessdate=19 February 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Lincolnshire County Council]] (Conservative controlled)<ref>{{cite news|author1=Stefan Pidluznyj|title=Passionate debate rages as Lincolnshire councillors broadly back leaving EU|url=http://thelincolnite.co.uk/2016/02/passionate-debate-rages-as-lincolnshire-councillors-broadly-back-leaving-eu/|accessdate=28 March 2016|work=The Lincolnite|date=19 February 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Portsmouth City Council]] (Conservative minority)<ref>{{cite news|author1=Economic Voice Staff|title=Portsmouth first City to vote to Leave the EU|url=http://www.economicvoice.com/portsmouth-first-city-to-vote-to-leave-the-eu/|accessdate=24 March 2016|work=The Economic Voice|date=23 March 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Thanet District Council]] (UKIP controlled)\n* [[Thurrock Council]] (UKIP \u2013 Conservative controlled)<ref>[http://www.ukip.org/thurrock_council_votes_in_favour_of_leaving_the_eu \"Thurrock Council votes in favour of leaving the EU\"]. ''UKIP''.</ref>\n\n===Organisations===\n\n====Trade unions====\n* [[Associated Society of Locomotive Engineers and Firemen]] (ASLEF)<ref>{{c