legraph.co.uk/news/2016/05/17/eu-referendum-boris-johnson-loch-ness-monster-brexit/}}</ref>\n*Sir [[Richard Dearlove]], former head of [[MI6]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=Dearlove|first1=Richard|title=Brexit would not damage UK security|url=http://www.prospectmagazine.co.uk/opinions/brexit-would-not-damage-uk-security|accessdate=24 March 2016|work=[[Prospect (magazine)|Prospect]]|date=23 March 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Charles Guthrie, Baron Guthrie of Craigiebank|Field Marshal Charles Guthrie, Baron Gutherie]], former [[Chief of the Defence Staff (United Kingdom)|Chief of Defence Staff]], [[British Army]], previously backed a remain vote<ref name=\"autogenerated2\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/06/17/field-marshal-lord-guthrie-why-i-now-back-the-leave-campaign/|title=Field Marshal Lord Guthrie: Why I now back the Leave campaign}}</ref>\n*[[Richard Heaslip|Rear Admiral Richard Heaslip]], senior Royal Navy officer<ref name=\"voteleavetakecontrol.org1\"/>\n*[[Roger Lane-Nott|Rear Admiral Roger Lane-Nott]], senior Royal Navy officer<ref name=\"voteleavetakecontrol.org1\"/>\n*[[Julian Thompson (Royal Marines officer)|Julian Thompson]], former Major General in the Royal Marines.<ref>[https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/defence/12176954/I-fought-for-Britain-and-I-know-how-the-EU-weakens-our-defences.html \"I fought for Britain and I know how the EU weakens our defences\"]. ''The Daily Telegraph''. 29 February 2016.</ref>\n*[[Jonathon Riley (British Army officer)|Lieutenant-General Jonathon Riley]], senior British Army officer and military historian<ref name=\"voteleavetakecontrol.org1\"/>\n*[[Michael Rose (British Army officer)|General Sir Michael Rose]], senior British Army officer<ref name=\"voteleavetakecontrol.org1\"/>\n*[[Nick Vaux|Major General Nick Vaux]], senior Royal Marine officer<ref name=\"voteleavetakecontrol.org1\"/>\n\nEconomists:\n*[[Roger Bootle]], economist<ref name=\"phillipinman\"/>\n*[[Bernard Connolly]], economist and former head o