itor<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/2/64e0ff1e-e1f6-11e5-9217-6ae3733a2cd1.html}}</ref>\n*[[Tim Stanley]], journalist<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/eureferendum/12165318/EU-summit-Camerons-deal-is-weak-weak-weak.-The-only-real-alternative-is-Brexit.html}}</ref>\n*[[Tom Utley]], journalist<ref name=\"betteroffout.net1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.betteroffout.net/supporters/academics-and-journalists/|title=Academics and journalists|accessdate=19 March 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160322002507/http://www.betteroffout.net/supporters/academics-and-journalists/|archive-date=22 March 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n*[[Sarah Vine]], columnist{{cn|date=March 2020}}\n*[[Milo Yiannopoulos]], journalist<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/Nero/status/703331924446732288|title=Milo Yiannopoulos \u2718 on Twitter|accessdate=23 June 2016}}{{Primary source inline|date=March 2020}}</ref>{{dead link|date=January 2018|fix-attempted=yes|bot=TweetCiteBot}}\n*[[Toby Young]], journalist and author<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.spectator.co.uk/2016/06/brexit-facts-not-fear/|title=Brexit: Facts Not Fear \u2013 Coffee House|date=14 June 2016|accessdate=23 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nWriters:\n*[[Tariq Ali]], writer and political activist<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/international/left-in-the-uk-is-divided-on-eu-membership/article8660901.ece|title=Left in the U.K. is divided on EU membership|date=29 May 2016|accessdate=23 June 2016|newspaper=The Hindu|last1=Menon|first1=Parvathi}}</ref>\n*[[Pat Condell]], writer<ref>{{cite tweet|user=patcondell|author=Pat Condell|number=727065269680635904|date=2 May 2016|title=Thanks to the #EU, we'll be seeing a lot more of this mentality in Europe, and in Britain, if we don't get out.}}</ref>\n*[[Tim Dawson]], screenwriter<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/Tim_R_Dawson/status/963755433277231104|title=Tim Dawson on Twitter}}{{Primary source inline|date=March 2020}}</ref>\n*[