s/documentsingle.aspx?DocumentID=398494|accessdate=29 April 2016|work=paulryan.house.gov|date=25 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160504044214/http://paulryan.house.gov/news/documentsingle.aspx?DocumentID=398494|archive-date=4 May 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* [[Vladimir Putin]], [[President of Russia]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Putin: Brexit or Remain \u2013 is up to British people to decide. Russia will respect any outcome|url=https://twitter.com/RussianEmbassy/status/744115248639123456|accessdate=18 June 2016|work=Twitter|date=25 April 2016}}{{Primary source inline|date=March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Organisations===\n* [[38 Degrees]] \u2013 supports giving clear information about the referendum and the European Union<ref>{{cite web|title=EU Referendum: The plan|url=https://speakout.38degrees.org.uk/campaigns/710|website=38 Degrees|accessdate=19 March 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Church of England]]<ref name=BBC2016-04-26 />\n*[[Open Europe]], think tank advocating [[Classical liberalism|liberal]], [[Free market|market-orientated]] and [[decentralising]] reforms within the European Union<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://us9.campaign-archive.com/?u=6d7abc505876d453ea030b48d&id=960c2fb55b|title=Message about Open Europe's stance in the upcoming EU referendum|website=us9.campaign-archive.com|access-date=5 August 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Patricia Scotland, Baroness Scotland of Asthal|Patricia Scotland, Baroness Scotland]], [[Commonwealth Secretary-General]], stated Commonwealth had no unified position on Britain should stay or go, but that the idea to replace the EU with the Commonwealth is a false choice.<ref>{{cite news|title= New Commonwealth chief says 'don't pit us against EU' in Brexit debate|url=http://ca.reuters.com/article/topNews/idCAKCN0X11FG|agency=Reuters Canada|date=4 April 2016}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{United Kingdom European Union membership referendum, 2016|state=expanded}}\n\n[[Category:2016 in Gibraltar]]\n[[Category:2016 in the United Kin