radio.jp/description/brave |title=Brave 10 on the radio @ HiBiKi |publisher=hibiki-radio.jp/ |accessdate=24 January 2012}}</ref> starring (Sarutobi Sasuke)\n*[[Fairy Tail]] Web Radio<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hibiki-radio.jp/description/fairytail |title= Fairy Tail&nbsp;\u2013 Web Radio @ HiBiKi |publisher=hibiki-radio.jp/ |accessdate=24 January 2012}}</ref> starring (Natsu Dragneel)\n\n===Dubbing===\n====Live-action====\n*''[[Admission (film)|Admission]]'' (Jeremiah Balakian ([[Nat Wolff]]))<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.star-ch.jp/channel/detail.php?movie_id=22751|title= \u30a2\u30c9\u30df\u30c3\u30b7\u30e7\u30f3\u3000\u2010\u89aa\u305f\u3061\u306e\u5165\u5b66\u8a66\u9a13\u2010|accessdate= 7 July 2019|work= Star Channel}}</ref>\n*''[[The Girl in the Spider's Web (film)|The Girl in the Spider's Web]]'' (Mikael Blomkvist ([[Sverrir Gudnason]]))<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.sonypictures.jp/he/2119167|title= \u8718\u86db\u306e\u5de3\u3092\u6255\u3046\u5973|accessdate= 21 May 2019|work= Sony Pictures Japan}}</ref>\n*''[[The Long Way Home (2015 film)|The Long Way Home]]'' (Kim Young-kwang ([[Yeo Jin-goo]]))<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.sonypictures.jp/he/2232155|title= \u897f\u90e8\u6226\u7dda\uff11\uff19\uff15\uff13|accessdate= 24 May 2019|work= Sony Pictures Japan}}</ref>\n<!-- \n*''[[And Then There Were None (miniseries)|And Then There Were None]]'' (Anthony Marston ([[Douglas Booth]]))\n*''[[I'm in the Band]]'' (Tripp Campbell ([[Logan Miller]]))<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.news-gate.jp/2010/1227/29/|title=Disney's 'I'm in the Band'&nbsp;\u2013 Tetsuya Kakihara's interview |date= 27 December 2010|accessdate=11 May 2012}}</ref>\n*''[[Meet Bill]]'' (The Kid ([[Logan Lerman]]))\n*''[[The Monuments Men]]'' (Pvt. Sam Epstein ([[Dimitri Leonidas]]))\n\n====Animation====\n*''[[Maya the Bee (2014 film)|Maya the Bee]]'' (Sting)\n*''[[Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles (2003 TV series)]]'' ([[Leonardo (Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles)|Leonardo]])\n*''[[Thunderbirds Are Go (TV series)|Thunderbirds Are Go]]'' ([[Gordon Tracy]])\n*''[[A Turtle's Tale: Sammy's Adventures]]'' (Ray) -->\n\n==Discography (as a singer)==\nKakihara released his debut mini-album, ''Still on Journey'', on 24 November 2010, which is produced by Kiramune Project. His second mini-album, ''Continuous'' was released on 15 February 2012, third mini-album, ''Call Me'', was released on 13 March2013, and fourth mini-album. \"\u30c0\u30f3\u30c7\u30a3\u30ae\u30fb\u30c0\u30f3 (Dandigi dan)\", was released on 30 July 2014. His first single (on the Kiramune label) is called \"String of pain\", released on 6 Februar 2013. It is the ending theme song for anime ''[[Hakkenden: Eight Dogs of the East]]'' in which he also voices the main role of Shino Inuzuka.\n\nHe also attended the following live music performances:\n\n*''Kiramune Live Music Festival 2010 (aka. Kira Fes)'', in which a DVD was released on 25 February 2011.\n:\u2013 Track list of Kakihara's Songs (in order of performance)*: 1. my life my time 2. Electric Monster 3. Endless Journey\n\n*''Kiramune Live Music Festival 2012'', held on 17 & 18 March 2012 in Japan. The DVD was released 24 August 2012.<ref>{{Cite web|title= DVD 'Kiramune Live Music Festival 2012' |url=http://shop.bandaivisual.co.jp/mall/shop?EcLogicName=catalog.detail&item_no=BCBE-4388|accessdate=18 April 2012}}</ref>\n:\u2013 Track list of Kakihara's Songs (in order of performance)*: 1.adrenaline 2.Good Luck 3.Chaos Breaker 4.Labyrinth 5.Bible of Heart 6.Hikari 7.thank you & smile 8.Continue\n\n*''Kiramune Live Music Festival 2013'', held on 13 & 14 April 2013 in Japan. The DVD release will be 6 November 2013.<ref>{{Cite web|title= DVD & Blu-ray \"Kiramune Live Music Festival 2013\"|url=http://kiramune.jp/news/index.php?subaction=showfull&id=1371881327&archive=&start_from=&ucat=2,3,4,7,8,11,12&|accessdate=20 July 2012}}</ref>\n*On 2 and 9 September 2012&nbsp;\u2013 he starred as lead singer in ''Joint Live 'Versus''', a live music event held by Kiramune.<ref>{{Cite web|publisher=Kiramune |title= Joint Live 'Versus' |url=http://kiramune.jp/event/versus/|accessdate=2 September 2012}}</ref> Track listing and event report: [http://kakiharainfo.blog.fc2.com/blog-entry-212.html]\n*On 7 ans 8 September 2013&nbsp;\u2013 he held his first solo live concert, called ''Kiramune Presents Tetsuya Kakihara First Live Generations''.<ref>{{Cite web|publisher=Kiramune |title= \uff1c\u67ff\u539f\u5fb9\u4e5f\uff0fKiramune Presents TETSUYA KAKIHARA First Live GENERATIONS\uff1e|url=http://kiramune.jp/news/index.php?subaction=showfull&id=1372647610&archive=&start_from=&ucat=2,8,9&|accessdate=20 July 2013}}</ref>\n\n=== Singles ===\n{|class=wikitable\n|-\n!Date released!!Title & track listing!!UPC/product code\n|-\n|6 February 2013||[[String of Pain]] <br /> 1. String of Pain <br /> 2. \u904b\u547d\u306e\u5f15\u529b <br /> 3. String of Pain (off vocal) <br /> 4. \u904b\u547d\u306e\u5f15\u529b (off vocal) <br /> ||LACM-14052\n|-\n|18 September 2013||[[GENERATIONS]]<br /> 1. GENERATIONS<br /> 2. U R my Sunshine! <br /> 3. \u30e9\u30d7\u30bd\u30c7\u30a3\u30fc (Rhapsody) <br /> ''DVD version: includes PV of \"Generations\", and trailers ''<br /> ||LACM-34128 \uff08Deluxe\uff09<br /> LACM-14128 \uff08Normal\uff09\n|-\n|15 April 2015<ref>http://kiramune.jp/artist/kakihara/disco.html#MUSICCLIP</ref>||\u54b2\u3044\u3061\u3083\u3044\u306a (Saichaina) <br />1. \u54b2\u3044\u3061\u3083\u3044\u306a (Saichaina)<br /> 2. world in bloom<br /> 3. Othello<br /> '''DVD version (Deluxe Edition)'''<br /> 1. \u54b2\u3044\u3061\u3083\u3044\u306a (Saichaina) (Music Clip)<br /> 2. TRAILER <br /> || \nLACM-34317 (Deluxe Edition)<br />\nLACM-14317 (Regular Edition)\n|-\n|15 June 2016||\u9032\u307e\u305b\u308d\uff01 (Susumasero\uff01) <br />1. \u9032\u307e\u305b\u308d\uff01 (Susumasero\uff01)<br /> 2. My way<br /> 3. \u78a7\u304f (Aoku)<br /> '''DVD version (Deluxe Edition)'''<br /> 1. \u9032\u307e\u305b\u308d! (Susumasero\uff01) (MUSIC CLIP)<br /> 2. TRAILER <br