] {{in lang|ja}}\n*[http://kakiharatetsuya.cocolog-nifty.com/blog/ Tetsuya Kakihara's official blog (previous one: Aug. 1 2008 ~ Aug. 1, 2013)\u00a0\u2013 Next One] {{in lang|ja}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20130502162006/http://www.81produce.co.jp/list.cgi?man+1112518134330 Tetsuya Kakihara] at [[81 Produce]] (archive page on 2 May 2013) -->\n*[http://gph.sakura.ne.jp/va_memo/system/vadb.cgi?action=view_ind&value=00748&namecode=1 Tetsuya Kakihara] at GamePlaza-Haruka Voice Acting Database {{in lang|ja}}\n*[http://www.usagi.org/doi-bin/seiyuu-lookup.pl?DB=anime&value=Tetsuya+Kakihara&N= Tetsuya Kakihara] at Hitoshi Doi's Seiyuu Database\n*{{ann|people|28816}}\n*{{IMDb name|id=2132616}}\n\n{{Seiyu Award for Best Rookie Actor}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kakihara, Tetsuya}}\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from D\u00fcsseldorf]]\n[[Category:Japanese male pop singers]]\n[[Category:Japanese male video game actors]]\n[[Category:Japanese male voice actors]]\n[[Category:Anime musicians]]\n[[Category:Lantis (company) artists]]\n[[Category:German expatriates in Japan]]\n[[Category:German people of Japanese descent]]\n[[Category:21st-century Japanese male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Japanese singers]]\n[[Category:Male actors of German descent]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n[[Category:81 Produce voice actors]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Tetsuya Kakihara\n| image              = <!-- filename only, no \"File:\" or \"Image:\" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] -->\n| alt                = <!-- descriptive text for use by the blind and visually impaired's speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \u67ff\u539f \u5fb9\u4e5f\n| native_name_lang   = ja\n| birth_name         = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1982|12|24}}\n| birth_place        = [[D\u00fcsseldorf]], [[West Germany]]\n| death_date         = <!-- {{Death date and age|df=y|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place        = \n| nationality        = \n| other_names        = {{plainlist|\n*Kakkii\n*{{Nihongo2|\u30ab\u30c3\u30ad\u30fc}} (nickname)\n}}\n| occupation         = {{flatlist|\n*[[Voice acting in Japan|Voice actor]]\n*singer\n}}\n| years_active       = 2002\u2013present\n| agent              = Zynchro\n| notable_works      = {{Plainlist|\n*''[[Fairy Tail]]'' as [[Natsu Dragneel]]\n*''[[Tengen Toppa Gurren Lagann]]'' as Simon\n}}\n| height             = 170 cm\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background         = solo_singer\n| genre              = [[J-pop]]\n| instrument         = Vocals\n| years_active       = 2010\u2013present\n| label              = Kiramune\n}}\n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''Tetsuya Kakihara'''|\u67ff\u539f \u5fb9\u4e5f|Kakihara Tetsuya|born 24 December 1982}} is a Japanese voice actor and singer. Previously affiliated with [[81 Produce]], he became a freelancer in June 2013.<ref>http://kakiharatetsuya.cocolog-nifty.com/blog/2013/07/post-9b74.html</ref> He set up his own agency, Zynchro, in July 2014.\n\nSince 2010, Kakihara has been affiliated with Kiramune, a music label by [[Bandai Visual]] and [[Lantis (company)|Lantis]], where he debuted as a singer with his first mini album, ''Still on Journey''. His first single, \"[[String of Pain]]\", released on 6 February 2013, is the ending theme song to the [[anime]] ''[[Hakkenden: Eight Dogs of the East]]'' in which he also voices the main role of Shino Inuzuka.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kiramune.jp/artist/kakihara/disco.html|title= Tetsuya Kakihara's first single \"String of pain\"., release on February 6, 2013|accessdate=18 January 2013}}</ref> He has released two full albums, five mini albums, and six singles. His third single, \"\u54b2\u3044\u3061\u3083\u3044\u306a (Saichaina)\", was released on 15 April 2015.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://kiramune.jp/artist/kakihara/disco.html#MUSICCLIP | title= Kakihara Tetsuya's 3rd single \"Saichaina\", release on April 15, 2015|publisher=Kiramune|accessdate=15 April 2015}}</ref>\n\nKakihara is well known for voicing roles as young boys with a fiery personality, like [[Natsu Dragneel]] from the anime ''[[Fairy Tail]]''. In games and drama CDs, he plays teenagers/mature roles, in which he employs his soft, sweet and mysterious voice, in [[otome game]]s like Shin from the [[PlayStation Portable|PSP]] game series ''[[Amnesia (visual novel)|Amnesia]]'', and K1-B0 from [[Danganronpa V3: Killing Harmony]]. Like other Japanese male voice actors, he is also active in [[Yaoi|BL (boys' love)]] Drama CDs and anime, and usually plays the ''uke'' part, like Akihito from ''[[Finder Series]]'', a work of popular boys love [[manga]] artist Ayano Yamane.\n\n==Biography==\nBefore becoming a voice actor, Kakihara had always longed to live in Japan. He was fascinated by entertainment culture; he thought Japan had funny television shows, and he has loved to read manga and watch anime since he was little. So with that in mind, he set off toward his goal to become a voice actor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.girls-style.jp/interview/002/01sop01_gs.php|title= \u3010Style of the PRINCE\u3011\u7b2c2\u56de\u30b2\u30b9\u30c8\uff1a\u67ff\u539f \u5fb9\u4e5f\u3055\u3093\u3000Vol.1 |accessdate=23 April 2012}}</ref> In 2001, Kakihara went to the Amusement Media Academy (a vocational school for voice actors and artists) to study voice acting. At first, it was not a smooth road for him to get in, as the school was surprised he actually came all the way from Germany after receiving a prompt email from him 3 days prior. Kakihara sincerely requested the school to accept his application, and when they officially accepted him, he found temporary housing at a friend's house.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.girls-style.jp/interview/002/01sop03_gs.php|title= \u3010Style of the PRINCE\u3011\u7b2c2\u56de\u30b2\u30b9\u30c8\uff1a\u67ff\u539f \u5fb9\u4e5f\u3055\u3093\u3000Vol.1 \u2013 pg 3|accessdate=23 April 2012}}</ref> While attending courses, he worked part-time jobs, and improved his Japanese through part-time school,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.girls-style.jp/interview/002/02sop01_gs.php|title= \u3010Style of the PRINCE\u3011\u7b2c2\u56de\u30b2\u30b9\u30c8\uff1a\u67ff\u539f \u5fb9\u4e5f\u3055\u3093\u3000Vol.2|accessdate=23 April 2012}}</ref> he debuted as a professional voice actor in 2003.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amgakuin.co.jp/contents/voice/ |title= \u30a2\u30df\u30e5\u30fc\u30ba\u30e1\u30f3\u30c8\u30e1\u30c7\u30a3\u30a2\u7dcf\u5408\u5b66\u9662 AMUSEMENT MEDIA Academy Official Website |accessdate=23 April 2012}}</ref>\n\nHe is nominated for the 'Best Male Newcomer/Rookie' award for his performance at the first [[Seiyu Awards]] in 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://av.watch.impress.co.jp/docs/20070303/seiyu.htm|title= \u7b2c1\u56de\u300c\u58f0\u512a\u30a2\u30ef\u30fc\u30c9\u300d\u65b0\u4eba\u8cde|accessdate=23 April 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Anime===\n;2003\n*''[[Monkey Typhoon]]'' (Announcer)\n\n;2004\n*''[[Doki Doki School Hours]]'' (Koro-chan)\n*''Nepos Napos'' (Timo)\n\n;2005\n*''[[Ah! My Goddess]]'' (Male Student)\n*''[[Fushigiboshi no Futagohime]]'' ([[List of Fushigiboshi no Futagohime characters#Jewelry Kingdom|Bright]])\n*''[[Magical Girl Lyrical Nanoha A's]]'' (L\u00e6vateinn, Graf Eisen, Landy/Randy(Operator B), Sand Dragon)\n\n;2006\n*''[[Ah! My Goddess: Flights of Fancy]]'' (Male Student)\n*''[[Black Lagoon]]'' (Rico, Ronnie, Ricardo)\n*''[[Fushigiboshi no Futagohime]] Gyu!'' (Bright)\n*''[[Kirarin Revolution]]'' (Toriya Kamiyama (ep 2))\n*''[[Princess Princess (manga)|Princess Princess]]'' (Yutaka Mikoto)\n\n;2007\n*''[[Dragonaut: The Resonance]]'' (Kazuki Tachibana)\n*''[[Magical Girl Lyrical Nanoha StrikerS]]'' (L\u00e6vateinn, Graf Eisen, Strada, Lat Cartos)\n*''[[Minami-ke]]'' (Fujioka)\n*''[[Prism Ark]]'' (Hyaweh)\n*''[[Romeo x Juliet]]'' (Mercutio)\n*''[[Tengen Toppa Gurren Lagann]]'' ([[Simon (Gurren Lagann)|Simon]])\n*''[[Zombie-Loan]]'' (Lyca)\n*''[[Claymore (manga)|Claymore]]'' (Orphelia's Brother)\n\n;2008\n*''[[Ga-Rei Zero]]'' (Masaki Shindou)\n*''[[Kannagi (manga)|Kannagi]]'' (Meguru Akiba)\n*''[[List of Kirarin Revolution characters#Other animal mascots|Kirarin Revolution Stage 3]]'' (Nii-kun)\n*''[[Linebarrels of Iron]]'' (Kouichi Hayase)\n*''[[Nabari no \u014c]]'' (S\u014dr\u014d Kat\u014d)\n*''[[Pok\u00e9mon (anime)|Pok\u00e9mon]]'': [[List of Pok\u00e9mon: Diamond and Pearl episodes|Diamond and Pearl]] (Reggie)\n*''[[Xam'd: Lost Memories]]'' (Shiroza)\n\n;2009\n*''[[Bleach (manga)|Bleach]]'' (Ggio Vega, Shinji)\n*''[[Cross Game]]'' (Mizuki Asami)\n*''[[Fairy Tail]]'' ([[Natsu Dragneel]])\n*''[[Fullmetal Alchemist: Brotherhood]]'' (Kain Fuery)\n*''[[Hanasakeru Seish\u014dnen]]'' (Toranosuke V Haga)\n*''[[Shangri-La (novel)|Shangri-La]]'' (Medusa)\n\n;2010\n*''[[Battle Spirits Trading Card Game|Battle Spirits Brave]]'' (Youth Glynnhorn)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sunrise-inc.co.jp/battlespirits3/character/04.html|title= Battle Spirits Brave \u2013 Anime Cast |accessdate=12 May 2012}}</ref>\n*''[[Beyblade: Metal Fusion]]'' (Hy\u014dma)\n*''[[Hime Chen! Otogi Chikku Idol Lilpri]]'' aka. Lilpri (Wish/Chris)\n*''[[Kaichou wa Maid-sama]]'' (Gouki Aratake)\n*''[[Nura: Rise of the Yokai Clan]]'' (Jiro Shima)\n\n;2011\n*''[[Ao no Exorcist]]'' (Amaimon)\n*''[[C (anime)]]'' (Kou Sennoza)\n*''Copihan'' (Omoto Kumogiri)\n*''[[Digimon Xros Wars: Time Traveling Hunter Boys]]'' (Ry\u014dma Mogami)\n*''[[Dog Days (Japanese TV series)|Dog Days]]'' (Gaul Galette des Rois)\n*''[[Fairy Tail]]'' (Natsu Dragneel, Natsu Dragion)\n*''HIGH SCORE'' (Tokiwazu Jiro)\n*''[[Moshidora]]'' (Keiichir\u014d Asano)\n*''[[Nura: Rise of the Yokai Clan]]: Demon Capital'' (Jiro Shima)\n*''[[Sengoku Paradise]]'' Kiwami ([[Date Masamune]]: refer to 'popular culture section')\n*''[[Sket Dance]]'' (Masafumi Usui)\n*''[[Toriko]]'' (Tom)\n\n;2012\n*''[[Brave10]]'' ([[Sarutobi Sasuke]])\n*''[[Detective Conan]]'' (Sumio Tateno (ep 665))\n*''[[Dog Days (Japanese TV series)|Dog Days\u2019]]'' (Gaul Galette des Rois)\n*''[[K (anime)|K]]'' (Colorless King, Adolf K. Weismann)\n*''[[Mobile Suit Gundam AGE]]'' (Deen Anon)\n*''[[Ozuma]]'' (Sam Coyne)\n*''[[Saint Seiya Omega]]'' (Ry\u016bh\u014d)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.toei-anim.co.jp/tv/seiya/staff.html |title= Saint Seiya Omega&nbsp;\u2013 Anime Cast |publisher= Toei Animation |accessdate=13 March 2012}}</ref>\n*''[[Smile PreCure!]]'' (Brian Taylor (ep 36))<ref>{{cite web|url=http://asahi.jp/precure/story/backnum_36.html|title=(Anime) Smile PreCure!&nbsp;\u2013 Brian Taylor (ep 36): Speaks in English|accessdate=26 October 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029200719/http://asahi.jp/precure/story/backnum_36.html|archivedate=29 October 2013}}</ref>\n\n;2013\n*''[[Amnesia (visual novel)|Amnesia]]'' (Shin)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.anime-amnesia.com/|title= AMNESIA&nbsp;\u2013 Anime Cast |accessdate=30 September 2012}}</ref>\n*''[[BlazBlue Alter Memory]]'' (Jin Kisaragi, Hakumen)\n*''[[Hakkenden: T\u014dh\u014d Hakken Ibun]]'' (Shino Inuzuka)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hakken-den.com/|title= Hakkenden: T\u014dh\u014d Hakken Ibun&nbsp;\u2013 Anime Cast |accessdate=30 September 2012}}</ref>\n*''[[Kamisama no Inai Nichiy\u014dbi]]'' (Kiriko Zubreska)\n*''[[Magi: The Kingdom of Magic]]'' (Kouha Ren)\n*''[[Makai Ouji: Devils and Realist]]'' (Camio)\n*''[[Minami-ke]]: Tadaima'' (Fujioka)\n*''[[Pretty Rhythm]]: Rainbow Live'' (K\u014dji Mihama)\n*''[[Servant x Service]]'' (J\u014dji Tanaka)\n*''[[Yowamushi Pedal]]'' (Toudou Jinpachi)\n*''[[A Simple Thinking About Blood Type]]'' (Type AB-kun)\n\n;2014\n*''[[Baby Steps]]'' (Takuya Miyagawa)\n*''[[Bonjour Sweet Love Patisserie|Bonjour\u266aSweet Love Patisserie]]'' (Mitsuki Aoi)<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news